  {"a":"locke","b":"aatrox","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Aatrox wants to hit all three Q edges and heal off you; sidestep the sweet spots and punish the long recovery with Q Ritual Nails autos so his sustain never gets going."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Purgatory totem drops him into execute range before his World Ender revive can bail him out, so an all-in here is your cleanest kill window of the lane."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you complete your first AP component his combo out-trades your poke, but your E Ashen Pursuit reset lets you dodge his sweet-spot Qs and stay even."},{"when":"Late","text":"Grouped, his revive plus healing sustains through fights while your burst gets kited; you need to isolate a target and blow R before he engages."}],"wants":{"you":["Sidestep Aatrox's Q sweet spots so he never heals","Land R Purgatory during his World Ender window","Use E to reset the dash-through and dodge his pull"],"foe":["Land all three Q edge hits to heal off you","Chain W Infernal Chains into a Q for a guaranteed sweet spot","Force extended trades where his passive and revive win"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a pure skill lane: Aatrox out-ranges you with Q but his early cooldowns are long, so trade with Ritual Nails autos when his Q is down and respect the sweet-spot heals.","mid":"Through 3-6 it stays even because he wants to land layered Q sweet spots while you weave in P Silver Stake on-hits and use E Ashen Pursuit to dodge them; whoever executes cleaner wins the exchange.","late":"After items his revive and healing let him grind through your burst unless you time R Purgatory on his World Ender, which is exactly your Level 6 edge before the game evens back out.","whys":["Skill lane at level 1 — long Aatrox cooldowns balance his Q range.","Level 2 stays even as both champs lack a hard commit tool.","Level 3 is a wash — his Q layering versus your on-hit poke.","Levels 4-5 remain skill-based around dodging his sweet spots.","Level 6 is even until you land R, but the totem execute tips this to you.","Locke favoured at 6 — R Purgatory executes through his revive window.","Post-items evens out as his sustain matches your burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"akali","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Akali wants to poke with Q Five Point Strike and heal, then all-in with E Shuriken Flip; hold your E Ashen Pursuit to dodge the flip's recast and she loses her engage."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Perfect Execution gives dashes, but your R Purgatory totem executes her out of her own shroud combo before her second cast lands — your kill window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With her first component her shroud plus burst can delete you, but you match her assassin pattern and your P Silver Stake chunks her low base HP."},{"when":"Late","text":"Both are squishy assassins; whoever lands their combo first wins. Track her energy and R charges and answer her all-in with your own."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge her E Shuriken Flip recast with your E blink","Land R Purgatory to execute through her W shroud","Punish her when her energy is empty after a Q-E combo"],"foe":["Land Q Five Point Strike at range to poke and heal","Use W Twilight Shroud to break your target and reposition","Chain both R Perfect Execution dashes onto you"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even: Akali's Q pokes and heals but costs heavy energy, so trade back with Ritual Nails autos and she can't sustain a war without going empty.","mid":"Through 3-6 it stays skill-based — she wants shroud-to-flip all-ins while you use E Ashen Pursuit to dodge and P Silver Stake to punish her thin HP bar; energy management decides it.","late":"After items it's a coinflip of assassin combos, but your Level 6 R Purgatory executes her before her shroud reset saves her, which is your one clear edge in an otherwise even fight.","whys":["Level 1 is even — Akali's energy cost caps her early poke.","Level 2 stays skill as neither has a reliable all-in yet.","Level 3 is a wash between her Q poke and your on-hit trades.","Levels 4-5 remain even around dodging her shroud engage.","Level 6 base is even until totems and ults trade.","Locke favoured — R Purgatory executes her through the shroud combo.","Late game evens back to a pure assassin coinflip."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"akshan","win":["Akshan","Akshan","Akshan","Akshan","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Akshan out-ranges you hard: his Q Avengerang pokes on the return path and his E Heroic Swing lets him kite over walls. You bleed HP trying to close the gap, so farm safe and don't force it."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Purgatory totem executes him before his E swing can carry him out of range — this is the phase you finally flip the lane in your favour."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once he has a component his swing-and-poke pattern still out-trades your poke, but you can look to E in when his Heroic Swing is on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Akshan's global R and camouflage passive make him a slippery duelist; you must catch him with E Ashen Pursuit and burst before he swings away."}],"wants":{"you":["Wait out his E Heroic Swing before committing your E blink","Land R Purgatory while his swing is on cooldown","Punish him at melee range where his poke pattern breaks down"],"foe":["Poke with Q Avengerang on both the throw and return","Kite with E Heroic Swing over terrain to reset distance","Use W camouflage passive to escape your ganks and burst"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour Akshan — his Q Avengerang double-hits and out-ranges every tool you have, so you eat poke while last-hitting and can't trade back without a clean gap-close.","mid":"Through 3-6 he stays ahead: Heroic Swing kites you around walls while his Q chunks you, and your E Ashen Pursuit alone can't out-mobility him unless he wastes his swing.","late":"His swing and camouflage keep him slippery, but at Level 6 your R Purgatory execute lands before he can swing to safety — that totem window is the one clear moment you turn the matchup.","whys":["Akshan favoured at 1 — his Q out-ranges all your poke.","Level 2 stays his as the double-hit Q keeps you at bay.","Level 3 favours Akshan once Heroic Swing lets him kite.","Levels 4-5 stay his with swing-and-poke out-trading you.","Level 6 base evens as both unlock their ultimates.","Locke favoured — R Purgatory executes before he can swing away.","Late evens out with his slipperiness against your burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"ambessa","win":["Ambessa","Ambessa","Ambessa","Ambessa","Ambessa","Ambessa","Ambessa"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ambessa's chained Q Cunning Sweep and W Repudiation out-damage your poke, and her dashes let her stick to you. Farm at max range and never sit in her Q spin radius."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Public Execution is a long-range dash-lock that starts the all-in before you can react; even your R Purgatory rarely lands the execute in time because she bursts you first."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Her Sundered Sky spike lets her heal through your combo and one-shot windows; you flat lose extended trades, so play for roam and scaling."},{"when":"Late","text":"Ambessa's mobility and burst make her a nightmare to peel; you need flash-R timing and jungle help to have any pick, never a solo fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Space outside her Q Cunning Sweep and W range at all times","Bait her R Public Execution before committing anything","Play safe and scale — look for roams over lane fights"],"foe":["Chain Q and W into her dash for a full damage combo","Lock you with R Public Execution to open the all-in","Use her dashes to close every gap your E creates"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 already favour Ambessa — her Q Cunning Sweep hits twice and her early damage plus dash pressure beat your Ritual Nails poke, so you concede space and just farm.","mid":"Through 3-6 she stays dominant: W Repudiation blocks and dashes keep her on top of you, and once her R comes online her all-in out-bursts anything your kit answers with.","late":"Ambessa scales into a mobile bruiser-assassin that heals and one-shots; your only path is spacing her cooldowns, baiting R, and pinging your jungler, because you lose the straight duel at every point.","whys":["Ambessa favoured at 1 — her double-hit Q beats your poke.","Level 2 stays hers as her dash damage out-trades you.","Level 3 favours Ambessa once her full chain combo is online.","Levels 4-5 stay hers with W block and sustained pressure.","Level 6 favours Ambessa — R Public Execution opens a lethal all-in.","First item keeps her ahead as Sundered Sky heals through your burst.","Late stays hers with mobility and burst you can't peel."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"aurora","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Aurora pokes with Q Twofold and W Across the Veil to reposition; respect her W dash-through spirits and use E Ashen Pursuit to close when her W is down, trading with P Silver Stake on-hits."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Between Worlds zones a big area, but your R Purgatory totem executes her mid-combo before she can W out — this is your cleanest kill window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With her first item her spirit-detonation burst can chunk you, but you match her as an assassin and your E reset keeps you slippery in the trade."},{"when":"Late","text":"Both are bursty mages/assassins; whoever lands their combo first wins. Track her W charges and answer her engage with your own all-in."}],"wants":{"you":["Close with E Ashen Pursuit when her W Across the Veil is down","Land R Purgatory to execute before she dashes out","Punish her long W cooldown with an on-hit trade"],"foe":["Poke with Q Twofold and build spirit stacks","Reposition and dodge with W Across the Veil","Zone you inside R Between Worlds during a fight"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even: Aurora's Q pokes but her W is her only escape, so when it's on cooldown you can walk her down with Ritual Nails autos and force a bad trade.","mid":"Through 3-6 it stays skill-based — she wants spirit poke and W repositioning while you use E Ashen Pursuit to punish her dash timing; whoever manages cooldowns cleaner takes the exchange.","late":"After items it's a bursty coinflip, but at Level 6 your R Purgatory execute lands before her W Across the Veil pulls her to safety, giving you the one clear edge in an otherwise even lane.","whys":["Level 1 is even — Aurora's poke matches your on-hit trades.","Level 2 stays skill as her W is her only real out.","Level 3 is a wash between her spirit poke and your pressure.","Levels 4-5 remain even around her W dash timing.","Level 6 base is even until ults and totems trade.","Locke favoured — R Purgatory executes before her W escape.","Late evens back to a bursty assassin coinflip."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"camille","win":["Camille","Camille","Camille","Camille","Camille","Skill","Camille"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Camille's Q Precision Protocol double-hit and W Tactical Sweep true-damage out-trade your poke, and her E Hookshot lets her engage over walls. Stay away from terrain and don't feed her sweet-spot W."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Hextech Ultimatum locks you in a zone for a full combo; your R Purgatory can answer if she commits low, so this phase is your one even window to trade totem for ult."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With her first component her Q-W burst plus shielding beats your damage, and Hookshot lets her stick through your E. Play safe and scale."},{"when":"Late","text":"Camille dives the backline and isolates you with R; you need to burst her before her second Q empowered hit lands or peel with jungle help."}],"wants":{"you":["Space away from walls so her E Hookshot can't engage","Trade only when her Q Precision Protocol is on cooldown","Save R Purgatory to answer her R Hextech Ultimatum"],"foe":["Land the W Tactical Sweep sweet spot for true damage","Engage over terrain with E Hookshot","Lock you with R Hextech Ultimatum for a guaranteed combo"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour Camille — her Q double-hit and early W chunk out-trade your Ritual Nails poke, and you have no wall-safe space, so you concede and farm carefully.","mid":"Through 3-6 she stays ahead: Hookshot engages you at will and her Q-W combo shreds your HP faster than P Silver Stake answers, so you play for scaling not trades.","late":"Camille out-duels and out-dives you at nearly every point; your Level 6 is the lone even window where R Purgatory can trade against her Ultimatum, but she reasserts control once items come online.","whys":["Camille favoured at 1 — her double-hit Q beats your poke.","Level 2 stays hers with early W true damage.","Level 3 favours Camille once Hookshot engages are online.","Levels 4-5 stay hers as Q-W combo out-trades you.","Level 6 favours Camille — R Hextech Ultimatum guarantees her combo.","First item is even — your R Purgatory can trade a totem for her Ultimatum.","Late favours Camille with her dive and isolation potential."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"cassiopeia","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Cassiopeia pokes with Q Noxious Blast and lays E Twin Fang on her W Miasma poison; dodge her grounding W so she can't stop your E Ashen Pursuit, then close and trade with P Silver Stake."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her R Petrifying Gaze stuns you if you face her, but if you flank or E behind, your R Purgatory totem executes her before she can chain E Twin Fang — a strong kill window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With her first item her Twin Fang DPS ramps hard if she keeps you poisoned, but you have kill pressure she lacks and your burst still beats her squishy frame."},{"when":"Late","text":"Cassiopeia becomes a grounding DPS turret; you must all-in through her W ground with E timing and burst her before Twin Fang stacks damage on you."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge her W Miasma so it can't ground your E blink","Flank her R Petrifying Gaze and E behind her","Land R Purgatory to execute her low-HP frame"],"foe":["Ground you with W Miasma to stop your E dash","Stack E Twin Fang on her poison for ramping DPS","Land R Petrifying Gaze while you face her to stun"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even but you have the edge in a fight: Cassiopeia's Q pokes yet her E needs a poison target, so when her W is down you can E in and out-trade her thin HP with Ritual Nails.","mid":"Through 3-6 it stays skill-based — she wants to ground you with W and ramp Twin Fang while you dodge the grounding and use P Silver Stake to punish; managing her W cooldown decides the trade and your kit tilts it your way.","late":"Her Twin Fang DPS scales but she stays squishy; at Level 6 your R Purgatory execute plus a flanking E beats her R Petrifying Gaze, which is why this lane and its 54% win rate lean in your favour.","whys":["Level 1 is even but your on-hit trade edges her thin frame.","Level 2 stays skill as her E needs a poison setup.","Level 3 is a wash around dodging her grounding W.","Levels 4-5 remain even as you punish her W cooldown.","Level 6 base is even until ults and totems trade.","Locke favoured — a flanking E plus R Purgatory beats her Gaze.","Late evens out as her ramping DPS meets your burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"chogath","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Cho'Gath","Skill","Cho'Gath","Cho'Gath"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your Q Ritual Nails poke wins the early trade window before Cho'Gath's Vorpal Spikes and Feast stacks give him permanent bulk, so shove and chip while he's small."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cho'Gath hits 6 and gains Feast — a point-and-click true-damage execute that also permanently grows his HP, which directly counters your R Purgatory threshold math by inflating the health pool you're trying to execute."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once Cho'Gath finishes an HP item plus a Feast stack or two, his effective health outruns your W Soul Ignition burst and your R threshold, so your all-in stops killing."},{"when":"Late","text":"Full-stack Feast Cho'Gath is a raid boss your execute totem can't reach — his HP is far above your R's growing threshold and his Q Rupture + Silence chains your engage into death."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade with Q Ritual Nails marks before he stacks Feast","Kill or force flash pre-6 to deny early Feast stacks","Roam and take side objectives instead of forcing a losing all-in"],"foe":["Land Q Rupture knock-up to set up his Feast execute","Stack Feast on minions and you to become unkillable","Scale HP items so your R threshold never catches him"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even skill — your P Silver Stake missing-HP procs and Q Ritual Nails poke actually chip Cho'Gath faster than his short-range Vorpal Spikes can answer, so freeze near your side and punish his last-hits. Avoid standing in the center of a caster wave where his Q Rupture can catch you.","mid":"By Levels 4-5 Cho'Gath tips ahead: Feast at 6 gives him a true-damage point-click execute plus permanent HP growth that neutralizes your R Purgatory math. Your W Soul Ignition self-damage is dangerous here because his Q Rupture + Silence can lock your E Ashen Pursuit escape and turn your grey-health into a real deficit. Only commit if you can burst him below Feast-execute range first.","late":"With items and Feast stacks Cho'Gath is a wall — his HP climbs far above your R's growing threshold so your execute totem simply won't trigger, and one Q Rupture into Feast deletes you. Don't force top; use your E mobility to roam and let your team peel him.","whys":["Level 1 is even — your Q poke and P on-hit trade evenly with his short-range Vorpal Spikes.","Level 2 stays even skill as neither champion has a real all-in threat yet.","Level 3 is still skill-based poke trading before Feast comes online.","Levels 4-5 favor Cho'Gath as he approaches 6 and Feast's HP growth starts outscaling your burst.","Level 6 is even in the immediate window since your R can still threaten before he stacks Feast.","First item favors Cho'Gath as HP items plus Feast stacks push his health past your R threshold.","2+ items belong to Cho'Gath — full Feast bulk makes your execute totem unable to reach his health pool."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"darius","win":["Darius","Darius","Darius","Darius","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Darius owns this range band — his Q Decimate outer-blade heal and W Crippling Strike slow mean any time you step in to Q Ritual Nails, he can pull with E Apprehension and start stacking Hemorrhage bleed on you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 evens out: your R Purgatory execute totem answers Darius's own Noxian Guillotine game, so the all-in becomes a coin flip on whose execute lands — respect his E pull and 5-stack bleed reset."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first AP item the matchup tips to you — R threshold plus W Soul Ignition burst and P missing-HP procs convert a caught Darius before his Guillotine resets."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game is even on positioning — if Darius lands E Apprehension into full bleed he kills you, but your R execute and E Ashen Pursuit reset let you pick him if he steps up alone."}],"wants":{"you":["Scale to your first item where R + W burst out-executes his Guillotine","Poke with Q marks from max range, never inside E pull range","Bait his E Apprehension then E Ashen Pursuit away from the bleed"],"foe":["Land E Apprehension pull to start Hemorrhage stacks","Stack 5 bleeds then reset his own Noxian Guillotine","Trade with Q Decimate outer-blade heal to win extended fights"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 belong to Darius. His Q Decimate outer-edge heals him in every trade and his E Apprehension can yank you out of position the moment you step up to Q Ritual Nails, letting him stack Hemorrhage and win the bleed war. Farm at max range, only take Q pokes when his E is on cooldown, and never sit in melee range where W Crippling Strike slows your escape.","mid":"Level 6 evens the fight. Your R Purgatory execute totem trades identity with Darius's Noxian Guillotine — the all-in becomes a coin flip on whose execute connects first. Make sure his E pull is down before you commit, because being apprehended into a bleed stack still kills you even with your ult up.","late":"Your first AP item tips things your way: R threshold plus W Soul Ignition and P Silver Stake missing-HP procs can convert a caught Darius before his Guillotine resets. Deeper into items it's even and positioning-decided — E Ashen Pursuit's takedown reset lets you dodge his pull and re-engage, but one clean E Apprehension into full Hemorrhage still deletes you.","whys":["Level 1 favors Darius — his Q heal and E pull dominate the melee range you need for Q.","Level 2 stays Darius as W Crippling Strike slow makes every trade bleed in his favor.","Level 3 favors Darius with full Hemorrhage stacking online and E pull threatening your poke.","Levels 4-5 remain Darius-favored before your ultimate arrives to answer his kill pressure.","Level 6 is even — your R Purgatory execute trades blows with his Guillotine reset game.","First item favors Locke as AP scaling lets your R threshold and W burst convert a caught Darius.","2+ items are even, decided by whether his E pull or your R execute lands first."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"drmundo","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Dr. Mundo"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Even skill window — your Q Ritual Nails poke and P Silver Stake missing-HP procs actually punish Mundo's passive-regen tankiness, but respect his Q Infected Bonesaw cleaver which chunks a percent of your HP and slows."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still even at 6 — your R Purgatory can threaten a low Mundo, but his R Maximum Dosage heals a huge chunk of max HP on cast, letting him climb back above your execute threshold mid-fight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Roughly even into first item as your AP burst still bites, but Mundo's regen and E Blunt Force Trauma missing-HP damage start closing the gap."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game tips to Mundo — his stacked HP and R Maximum Dosage overheal outrun your R threshold, and his passive shrugs off your CC while E scales its damage off his own huge health bar."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke with Q + P missing-HP procs before his regen ramps","Bait his Q Infected Bonesaw cleaver then E Ashen Pursuit in","Force a kill or big lead before his HP items and R overheal come online"],"foe":["Land Q Infected Bonesaw cleaver for percent-HP poke and slow","Cast R Maximum Dosage to overheal above your execute threshold","Stack HP so E Blunt Force Trauma and his bulk outscale your burst"]},"early":"Levels 1-5 are an even, skill-based lane. Your Q Ritual Nails and P Silver Stake missing-HP on-hit are two of the few tools that actually pressure a passive-regen tank, so trade whenever his Q Infected Bonesaw cleaver is on cooldown and deny him free stacking. Don't stand in the cleaver's path — it deals percent-max-HP and slows you into his walk-up.","mid":"Level 6 stays even. Your R Purgatory threatens a low Mundo, but the instant he casts R Maximum Dosage he overheals a large chunk of max HP and climbs back above your execute threshold, so time your ult for after his R or bait it out. Your W Soul Ignition self-damage is risky here because his sustained cleaver poke can leave you unable to afford the grey-health cost.","late":"Late game belongs to Dr. Mundo. Stacked HP items plus R Maximum Dosage overheal push his effective health far past your R's growing threshold, his passive tosses your CC on the ground, and E Blunt Force Trauma scales harder as his own health balloons. Look to roam and take side lanes rather than solo-killing an untouchable Mundo.","whys":["Level 1 is even — your Q and P missing-HP procs pressure his regen as well as his cleaver pressures you.","Level 2 stays even skill with no decisive spike for either side.","Level 3 is even — poke trades roughly balance his percent-HP cleaver.","Levels 4-5 remain even as your burst still matches his early bulk.","Level 6 is even — your R threat is answered by his R Maximum Dosage overheal.","First item is even, your AP burst still biting against his ramping regen.","2+ items favor Dr. Mundo — stacked HP and overheal outrun your R execute threshold."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"fiora","win":["Fiora","Fiora","Fiora","Fiora","Skill","Skill","Fiora"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Fiora dominates this band — her Q Lunge and E Bladework let her walk up, proc Vitals, and W Riposte your Q Ritual Nails or any commit while her passive true-damage shreds you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 evens: your R Purgatory execute totem gives you a real all-in answer to her sustain, but her Grand Challenge Vitals heal can pull her back above your threshold if you mistime it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Roughly even into first item as your AP R and W burst can convert a caught Fiora, but she can still W Riposte your key ability to negate the kill."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game returns to Fiora — her R Grand Challenge sustain and W Riposte stun on your engage let her outlast and flip your all-in, especially if she dodges your R timing."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 6 so R Purgatory answers her sustain","Dodge her W Riposte window before committing burst","Poke with Q from range and E Ashen Pursuit out of Lunge range"],"foe":["Proc Vitals with Q Lunge and E Bladework","W Riposte your Q or all-in to parry and stun","Sustain through R Grand Challenge to outlast your burst"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 belong to Fiora. She walks up with Q Lunge, procs her passive Vitals for true damage, and holds W Riposte to parry and stun whatever you commit — including your Q Ritual Nails cast or your W Soul Ignition all-in. Farm carefully, keep your E Ashen Pursuit up as an escape, and never blow a key ability while her Riposte is available.","mid":"Level 6 is your even window. R Purgatory finally gives you an execute answer to her sustain and duel pressure. But her R Grand Challenge heals off proccing Vitals, so if you ult too early she heals back above your threshold — burst her down with W and P missing-HP procs first, then drop the totem, and only after her W Riposte is spent.","late":"Late game swings back to Fiora. Grand Challenge sustain plus a well-held W Riposte on your engage lets her parry your burst and outlast your R threshold. Your first-item burst can still convert a caught Fiora, but if she reads your R timing or parries your commit she flips the duel. Pick isolated angles and use E's takedown reset to disengage when the parry is up.","whys":["Level 1 favors Fiora — Q Lunge and Vitals procs win the walk-up before you have tools.","Level 2 stays Fiora as E Bladework and Riposte threat dominate trades.","Level 3 favors Fiora with full Vitals shredding and W parry online.","Levels 4-5 remain Fiora-favored before your ult arrives to answer her.","Level 6 is even — R Purgatory gives you an execute answer to her sustain.","First item is even as your AP burst can convert a caught Fiora despite her parry.","2+ items favor Fiora — R sustain and a held Riposte outlast and flip your all-in."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"galio","win":["Galio","Galio","Galio","Galio","Skill","Skill","Galio"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Galio owns this range — his W Shield of Durand magic resist plus passive Colossal Smash on-hit makes him nearly immune to your Q Ritual Nails and W Soul Ignition magic burst while he pokes with Q Winds of War."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 evens out: your R Purgatory execute answers a low Galio, but his W damage-reduction and E Justice Punch knockup can eat your combo and set up his own all-in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Roughly even into first item — with Magic Pen your AP finally bites through his W, letting your R threshold convert a caught Galio."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game returns to Galio — his W magic-resist wall and global R Hero's Entrance make him tanky and slippery, and his built-in MR outscales your single-target magic burst."}],"wants":{"you":["Buy Magic Pen so your kit bites through W Shield of Durand","Reach 6 where R Purgatory answers his sustain","Poke with Q + P missing-HP when his W is down"],"foe":["Hold W Shield of Durand to negate your magic burst","Land E Justice Punch knockup to start his all-in","Stack MR/HP so your single-target AP never converts"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 belong to Galio. His W Shield of Durand gives huge magic damage reduction exactly when you want to Q Ritual Nails or W Soul Ignition, so your entire magic kit bounces off while his passive Colossal Smash and Q Winds of War poke you down. Farm at range, save your burst for when his W is on cooldown, and don't waste W self-damage into his shield.","mid":"Level 6 evens the lane. R Purgatory finally threatens a low Galio, but he can pop W to survive your combo and answer with E Justice Punch knockup into his own engage. Bait his W first, then commit your burst plus P Silver Stake missing-HP procs, and hold R for after his damage-reduction window ends.","late":"Late game swings back to Galio. His W magic-resist wall and natural MR make your single-target AP burst struggle to reach your R threshold, and global R Hero's Entrance lets him disengage or roam away from your picks. Buying Magic Pen keeps you relevant, but focus on roaming with E and grouping rather than solo-killing a tanky, slippery Galio.","whys":["Level 1 favors Galio — W Shield of Durand and Colossal Smash blunt your magic damage.","Level 2 stays Galio as Q Winds of War poke outranges your walk-up.","Level 3 favors Galio with full W uptime negating your burst windows.","Levels 4-5 remain Galio-favored before your ult gives you a kill answer.","Level 6 is even — R Purgatory threatens a low Galio despite his W.","First item is even as Magic Pen lets your R threshold convert a caught Galio.","2+ items favor Galio — his MR wall and global R outscale your single-target burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"gangplank","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Gangplank"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Even skill lane — your Q Ritual Nails and P missing-HP procs out-trade GP's early Q Parrrley, but respect his W Remove Scurvy cleanse of your Q slow and his barrel setups."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still even at 6 — your R Purgatory can execute a low GP, but his R Cannon Barrage slow zone and barrel chains let him disengage or answer your dive."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Roughly even into first item as your AP burst still converts a caught GP, but his crit-Parrrley and barrel damage begin to spike."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game tips to Gangplank — his stacked barrel combos, crit Q poke, and global R pressure let him out-DPS and out-scale your single-target burst, and W cleanses your Q slow to escape your all-in."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade with Q + P missing-HP before his barrels come online","Kill the barrel before it detonates to deny his combo","Force fights before his crit and barrel scaling spike"],"foe":["Chain barrels for AoE knockup and burst","W Remove Scurvy to cleanse your Q slow and escape","Scale crit Parrrley + global R into unkillable poke"]},"early":"Levels 1-5 are an even, skill-based lane. Your Q Ritual Nails and P Silver Stake missing-HP on-hit out-trade Gangplank's early Q Parrrley pokes, so pressure him whenever his barrels aren't set. The key skill test is his kegs — shoot or dodge the barrel before it detonates, and don't sit in a spot where he can chain two into a knockup during your walk-up.","mid":"Level 6 stays even. R Purgatory lets you execute a low Gangplank, but his R Cannon Barrage drops a global slow zone he can use to peel your dive or set up his own barrel chain. Bait his W Remove Scurvy or catch him without it, since it cleanses your Q slow and undoes your engage. Time your burst around detonated barrels, not into them.","late":"Late game belongs to Gangplank. Stacked barrel combos, crit Parrrley poke, and global R pressure let him out-DPS and out-scale your single-target AP burst, while W Remove Scurvy cleanses your Q slow to slip your all-in. Your R can still snipe a low GP in a fight, but don't try to solo-kill a fed one — roam with E Ashen Pursuit and use your execute in teamfights instead.","whys":["Level 1 is even — your Q and P out-trade his early Parrrley.","Level 2 stays even skill with neither side spiking.","Level 3 is even as barrel play balances your poke.","Levels 4-5 remain even before his scaling comes online.","Level 6 is even — R Purgatory execute matches his R disengage.","First item is even, your AP burst still converting a caught GP.","2+ items favor Gangplank — barrel combos, crit poke, and global R outscale your burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"garen","win":["Garen","Garen","Garen","Garen","Garen","Garen","Garen"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Garen dominates every trade — his W Courage damage reduction plus passive Perseverance regen shrug off your Q Ritual Nails poke, while Q Decisive Strike silences your abilities and lets him E Judgment spin you down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 stays Garen's — his R Demacian Justice is a max-HP-percent execute that punishes your squishy AP frame, and his W blunts your R Purgatory setup burst."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still Garen — his W damage reduction and regen let him tank your combo, and Q silence shuts off your E Ashen Pursuit escape into his E spin."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game remains Garen — stacked HP/resists plus W Courage make him near-immune to your single-target magic burst, and his R execute scales with your missing HP just like your own kit wishes it did."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke with Q + P missing-HP only when his W and Q are down","Never get silenced by Q Decisive Strike before you E out","Roam with E Ashen Pursuit rather than force a losing all-in"],"foe":["Q Decisive Strike silence to shut off your abilities and slow","W Courage + Perseverance to tank your burst and out-sustain","R Demacian Justice percent-HP execute on your squishy frame"]},"early":"Levels 1-5 belong hard to Garen. His W Courage damage reduction and passive Perseverance regen erase your Q Ritual Nails poke, and the moment you step up his Q Decisive Strike silences your kit and speeds him into E Judgment, spinning you down before you can W Soul Ignition safely. Farm at absolute max range, respect the silence, and keep E Ashen Pursuit ready purely as an escape.","mid":"Level 6 does not save you — this is the opposite of most matchups. Garen's R Demacian Justice is a point-click percent-max-HP execute tailor-made to delete your squishy AP frame, and his W blunts the burst you need to set up your own R Purgatory. Don't trade into his ult range; if you commit and fail to kill through his W, he simply executes you back.","late":"Late game stays Garen's. Stacked HP and resists under W Courage make him nearly immune to your single-target magic burst, so your R threshold rarely catches him while his R execute always catches you. Give up solo pressure top — use E's takedown reset to roam and contribute picks elsewhere, and let your team deal with the bruiser you can't crack.","whys":["Level 1 favors Garen — W Courage and Perseverance shrug off your poke.","Level 2 stays Garen as Q Decisive Strike silence shuts down your trades.","Level 3 favors Garen with full E Judgment spin damage in melee.","Levels 4-5 remain Garen-favored as his sustain outlasts your burst.","Level 6 favors Garen — R Demacian Justice percent-HP execute deletes your squishy frame.","First item favors Garen as W damage reduction tanks your combo.","2+ items stay Garen — stacked resists under W make him near-immune to your magic burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"gnar","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Mini Gnar out-ranges you with Boomerang Throw (Q) and Hyper (E) kiting, so respect his poke and use E Ashen Pursuit only to close when his Q is on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Purgatory (R) totem is a real kill button here: mini Gnar is squishy and once he dips under the growing execute threshold you delete him before he can build Rage into Mega form."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After your first AP item plus W Soul Ignition grey-health steroid you burst mini Gnar in one combo; just avoid all-inning while his Rage bar is full."},{"when":"Late","text":"Mega Gnar with GNAR! (R) stun into a wall flips fights, so save E to dash through and reset off a takedown rather than eating the crowd control."}],"wants":{"you":["Catch him in mini form under your R threshold","Bait out Boomerang (Q) then E in","Fight while his Rage bar is low"],"foe":["Kite with Hyper (E) and Q pokes","Transform to Mega and land GNAR! (R) into terrain","Stall lane until his tank Mega windows"]},"early":"Mini Gnar's Boomerang (Q) and Hyper (E) win the poke war early, so farm safe, keep P Silver Stake chip on when you can trade, and don't force E Ashen Pursuit into a full Rage bar. Levels 1-2 are pure skill — match cooldowns and avoid the double-Q return hit.","mid":"By 6 the matchup tilts to you: mini Gnar is a squishy target and Purgatory (R) executes him the moment he crosses the rising threshold. Bait his Boomerang, W for grey-health, then E in and finish — just track his Rage so you never all-in as he flips to Mega.","late":"With items it stays roughly even. Your burst still kills mini Gnar instantly, but Mega Gnar's GNAR! (R) stun and tankiness let him survive and turn, so pick your reset windows with E and don't dive into a wall.","whys":["Level 1 is even — both trade with basic pokes and no engage tools online.","Level 2 stays skill-based as mini Gnar's Q return damage offsets your P chip.","Level 3 is even — his Hyper (E) kiting matches your E gap-close.","Levels 4-5 remain a skill poke war with neither side committing.","Level 5 into 6 is even until your ult comes online.","At 6 you're favoured — Purgatory (R) executes squishy mini Gnar under the threshold.","2+ items returns to skill as Mega Gnar's stun and bulk let him survive your burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"gragas","win":["Gragas","Gragas","Gragas","Gragas","Gragas","Gragas","Gragas"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Gragas bullies you with Barrel Roll (Q) poke and Body Slam (E) trades that proc his Happy Hour (W) sustain, out-healing your P Silver Stake chip and shoving you off the wave."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His Explosive Cask (R) is the problem for your all-in: even under your Purgatory (R) threshold he can knock you out of totem range, and his W shield eats your W Soul Ignition burst."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Gragas out-scales your early spike as a durable mage — his Q max-range poke and Rylai's-style slows kite your E Ashen Pursuit and he simply out-sustains the poke war."},{"when":"Late","text":"He becomes a peel and displacement machine; Explosive Cask (R) flips any dive on your carries and his bulk means your execute rarely lands before he Body Slams away."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Barrel Roll (Q) and punish the cooldown","Save E to dash the moment he Body Slams (E) in","All-in only when his W and R are down"],"foe":["Poke with Q and heal on you via W","Cask (R) you out of Purgatory range","Sustain the wave and scale into a durable mage"]},"early":"Gragas owns levels 1-2: his Barrel Roll (Q) out-ranges everything you have and Happy Hour (W) refunds the trade damage your P chips in. Don't walk up to last-hit into a charged Q, and never contest melee range while his Body Slam (E) is up.","mid":"This stays Gragas-favoured through 6. His W shield and sustain blunt your W Soul Ignition all-in, and Explosive Cask (R) can knock you clean out of Purgatory (R) totem range right as you commit. Only look for a kill if you bait both his E and R first.","late":"With items Gragas remains ahead — he's a bulky mage with a game-swinging displacement ult, and your assassin burst struggles to execute him before he slows and Body Slams to safety. Play for roams and side-lane picks rather than the straight 1v1.","whys":["Level 1 is Gragas — Barrel Roll (Q) out-ranges you and starts the chip war.","Level 2 is Gragas as Body Slam (E) plus W sustain wins the melee trade.","Level 3 stays Gragas with full poke-and-heal pressure on the wave.","Levels 4-5 favour Gragas — his sustain undoes your P damage.","Level 6 is Gragas because Cask (R) knocks you out of your execute range.","First item keeps Gragas ahead as his durability blunts your burst spike.","2+ items is Gragas — he out-scales as a tanky mage you can't cleanly execute."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"graves","win":["Graves","Graves","Graves","Graves","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Graves shreds you early: End of the Line (Q) burst plus Smoke Screen (W) blind and slow means his auto trades win, and Quickdraw (E) dashes give him the armor and mobility to out-duel your walk-ups."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Purgatory (R) flips it — Graves is squishy, and once he's under the execute threshold your W plus R totem kills him through his dash before he can Quickdraw to safety."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After your first AP item you out-burst him: E Ashen Pursuit in on Silver Stake stacks, W Soul Ignition, and execute before his double-shot Q can chunk you back."},{"when":"Late","text":"Skill-based late — Graves does massive item damage, so blind windows (W) and his E armor stacks decide it; catch him before he can Smoke Screen and kite your E."}],"wants":{"you":["Wait for 6 and execute under Purgatory (R)","E in when his Quickdraw (E) is on cooldown","Dodge Smoke Screen (W) so you keep your autos"],"foe":["Trade with Q burst and W blind pre-6","Use Quickdraw (E) armor to win early duels","Kite your all-in with Smoke Screen slow"]},"early":"Graves runs you over levels 1-4: End of the Line (Q) does heavy burst, Smoke Screen (W) blinds your autos and cuts your P Silver Stake damage, and Quickdraw (E) gives him armor and a dash to win every early trade. Farm respectfully and don't E in while his kit is up.","mid":"The corner is level 6. Graves is squishy, so Purgatory (R) turns him into an execute target — bait or dodge his Smoke Screen, E through, W for grey-health, and finish him under the rising threshold before Quickdraw resets. Levels 4-5 are a coin-flip skill window as your ult comes online.","late":"With items it's skill-based. Graves' auto damage is lethal, but your burst-and-execute pattern still deletes him if you catch him with W on cooldown; respect his blind and armor stacks and pick your engage rather than trading autos head-on.","whys":["Level 1 is Graves — his Q burst and auto damage out-trade your chip.","Level 2 is Graves as Smoke Screen (W) blind shuts off your P autos.","Level 3 is Graves with Quickdraw (E) armor winning the duel.","Levels 4-5 stay Graves-favoured on raw early trading power.","Level 5 is even — your ult is coming and his lead thins.","At 6 you're favoured — Purgatory (R) executes the squishy Graves.","2+ items is skill as his item damage offsets your reliable burst execute."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"gwen","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Gwen's Snip Snip! (Q) does the true-damage burst and Hallowed Mist (W) makes her untargetable to your abilities inside the cloud, so trade at Q range and don't E Ashen Pursuit into her W bubble."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Purgatory (R) is your edge — Gwen has no health steroid, so once she drops under the growing execute threshold your totem finishes her even if she Skip 'n Slash (E) dashes."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first AP item plus W Soul Ignition out-bursts her: catch her outside Hallowed Mist, E in on Silver Stake stacks, and delete her before her Q ramps."},{"when":"Late","text":"Even late — Gwen's Needlework (R) triple-throw and W untargetability are strong, so time your all-in for when her W is down and execute through the ult zone."}],"wants":{"you":["Fight her outside Hallowed Mist (W)","Execute under Purgatory (R) at 6","E in when her Skip 'n Slash (E) is down"],"foe":["Sit in Hallowed Mist to dodge your spells","Poke with Snip Snip! (Q) true damage","Scale with on-hit and Needlework (R)"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are skill: Gwen pokes with Snip Snip! (Q) and can hide inside Hallowed Mist (W) where none of your abilities land, but she has no early sustain so your P Silver Stake chip keeps trades fair. Bait her W, respect the Q true damage, and farm even.","mid":"At 6 you pull ahead. Gwen lacks a healing steroid, so Purgatory (R) reliably executes her under the rising threshold — E in when her Skip 'n Slash is on cooldown, W for grey-health, and finish before she can bubble W. Levels 4-5 stay a skill matchup until your ult lands.","late":"With items it's roughly even. Gwen's Needlework (R) and W untargetability give her outs, but your burst-into-execute still kills her if you engage while W is down. Play around her Mist timer rather than trading into it.","whys":["Level 1 is even — both poke with no engage online.","Level 2 stays skill as her Q true damage matches your P chip.","Level 3 is even — Hallowed Mist (W) offsets your E gap-close.","Levels 4-5 remain skill-based with neither committing.","Level 5 is even until your ult comes online.","At 6 you're favoured — Purgatory (R) executes steroid-less Gwen.","2+ items returns to skill as her W and Needlework (R) give her escape outs."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"heimerdinger","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Heimerdinger walls you off with H-28G Turrets (Q) and pokes with Hextech Micro-Rockets (W), so clear a turret before you commit and don't E Ashen Pursuit into a full turret nest."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Purgatory (R) is your kill window — Heimer is immobile and squishy, so E through his turret line, W Soul Ignition, and execute him under the threshold before he CH-2 Grenades (E) you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first AP item lets you one-combo him: bait or dodge his E stun, E in on Silver Stake stacks, and delete him before UPGRADE!!! (R) super-turrets can zone you."},{"when":"Late","text":"Even late — his upgraded turrets and E stun zone objectives hard, so flank from fog and execute rather than walking down the turret line."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge CH-2 Grenade (E) then E in","Execute the immobile Heimer under Purgatory (R)","Kill him before he re-deploys turrets"],"foe":["Wall the lane with H-28G Turrets (Q)","Land the CH-2 Grenade (E) stun to peel your dash","Poke with W rockets and zone with R turrets"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are skill: Heimerdinger denies you range with H-28G Turrets (Q) and chips with Micro-Rockets (W), but he's completely immobile. Clear a turret, dodge his CH-2 Grenade (E), and use P Silver Stake chip on him whenever he steps up to shove.","mid":"At 6 you spike. Heimer has zero mobility, so Purgatory (R) executes him cleanly — E through the turret line, dodge his E stun, W for grey-health, and finish him under the threshold. Levels 4-5 stay a skill lane about clearing turrets and dodging his grenade.","late":"With items it's roughly even. His UPGRADE!!! (R) super-turrets and E stun make a straight walk-down dangerous, but your E blink lets you flank the immobile target and execute him from an angle his turrets don't cover.","whys":["Level 1 is even — his turret range trades against your melee threat.","Level 2 stays skill as W rockets match your P chip.","Level 3 is even — his turret nest offsets your E gap-close.","Levels 4-5 remain skill-based about turret clear and grenade dodging.","Level 5 is even until your ult comes online.","At 6 you're favoured — Purgatory (R) executes the immobile Heimer.","2+ items returns to skill as super-turrets and E stun zone your approach."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"illaoi","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Never fight Illaoi in her tentacles — Tentacle Smash (W) plus Harsh Lesson (E) rip a spirit out of you and she out-sustains any prolonged trade, so dodge Test of Spirit (E) and trade only when tentacles are down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Purgatory (R) is your answer to her all-in — if she Leaps of Faith (R) onto you, E out with Ashen Pursuit, then re-engage and execute her under the threshold once her tentacle wall expires."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first AP item plus W Soul Ignition lets you burst her between tentacle windows; catch her mid-cooldown, E in, and finish before she can pull your spirit."},{"when":"Late","text":"Even late — her R tentacle field is lethal in a brawl, so use E mobility to fight her outside the field and execute rather than standing in the slam zone."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Test of Spirit (E) and fight off tentacles","Execute under Purgatory (R) between W windows","Use E to escape her Leap of Faith (R)"],"foe":["Pull your spirit with Test of Spirit (E)","Brawl inside her tentacle field","Sustain through trades and all-in at 6"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are skill and it's all about the tentacles: Illaoi's Tentacle Smash (W) and Harsh Lesson (E) out-trade you and her passive sustain refills whatever your P Silver Stake chips away. Dodge her Test of Spirit skillshot, poke when tentacles are on cooldown, and don't get greedy in melee.","mid":"At 6 you tip ahead. Her Leap of Faith (R) all-in is scary, but you have the mobility to E out of the tentacle field, then re-engage and execute her under Purgatory (R) once the slams stop. Bait her E, W for grey-health, and finish between windows. Levels 4-5 stay a skill lane about spacing the tentacles.","late":"With items it's roughly even. Illaoi's R field wins any stand-still brawl, but your E blink lets you fight her outside the tentacles and execute a target with no dash to chase you. Never all-in into a fresh R.","whys":["Level 1 is even — no tentacles up yet, both trade basics.","Level 2 stays skill as her W sustain matches your P chip.","Level 3 is even — her tentacle trades offset your E gap-close.","Levels 4-5 remain skill-based about dodging Test of Spirit.","Level 5 is even until your ult comes online.","At 6 you're favoured — E escapes her R and Purgatory executes her.","2+ items returns to skill as her R field wins the stationary brawl."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"irelia","win":["Irelia","Irelia","Irelia","Irelia","Irelia","Irelia","Irelia"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Irelia snowballs the moment she has stacks — Bladesurge (Q) resets off minions and your body, Defiant Dance (W) gives a huge damage-reduction shield through your combo, and Flawless Duet (E) stuns you out of any all-in."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Her Vanguard's Edge (R) wall zones your Purgatory (R) and cuts you off; she can Q-reset onto you and W-tank your W Soul Ignition burst so your execute rarely gets the finish."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Irelia out-scales your early spike as a reset-duelist — her sustained on-hit plus W shield beats your one-combo burst, and she stat-checks you the moment she's ahead."},{"when":"Late","text":"She's a lane bully who snowballs into a hyper-mobile duelist; her Q resets and E stun mean your E Ashen Pursuit engage gets punished before your execute lands."}],"wants":{"you":["Only fight when her Bladesurge (Q) has no reset target","Bait Defiant Dance (W) before you W in","E away from her Flawless Duet (E) stun"],"foe":["Reset Q off minions and your champion","Shield your burst with Defiant Dance (W)","Stun your all-in with Flawless Duet (E) and R"]},"early":"Irelia beats you from level 1: Bladesurge (Q) resets keep her sticky and topped up, and once she gets a couple of stacks her trades snowball out of control. Deny her Q reset targets by managing the wave, respect the Flawless Duet (E) stun, and don't feed her passive stacks with careless P trades.","mid":"Through 6 she stays ahead. Defiant Dance (W) shields straight through your W Soul Ignition combo, and her Vanguard's Edge (R) wall can cut off your Purgatory execute and Q-reset her onto you. Only commit if her W and E are both down, otherwise she stat-checks the all-in.","late":"With items Irelia remains favoured — she's a reset-fuelled duelist whose on-hit and shielding out-value your burst-execute pattern. Play safe, look to roam or group, and pick her only when she's already used W and E rather than dueling her head-on.","whys":["Level 1 is Irelia — Bladesurge (Q) resets keep her sticky and ahead.","Level 2 is Irelia as her stacked trades snowball on you.","Level 3 is Irelia with Defiant Dance (W) shielding your damage.","Levels 4-5 favour Irelia — Flawless Duet (E) stun punishes your engage.","Level 6 is Irelia because R walls off your Purgatory execute.","First item keeps Irelia ahead as her sustain beats your one-combo burst.","2+ items is Irelia — she out-scales as a reset duelist you can't cleanly kill."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"jax","win":["Jax","Jax","Jax","Jax","Jax","Jax","Jax"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Jax's E Counter Strike stun is the whole matchup: if you commit Q Ritual Nails and E Ashen Pursuit into an active Counter Strike, he eats all your basics, stuns you, and W-Empowered Strikes you to death. Never dash in while E is up."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Jax's R Grandmaster's Might flips his resists and adds on-hit magic burst; even landing your R Purgatory totem, his sustained trades out-heal your grey-health W window and he wins the extended all-in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Jax scales harder than you off a single Blade of the Ruined King or Trinity spike, turning his stun-window into a kill every time it's up while your assassin burst falls off against his resists."},{"when":"Late","text":"In extended fights Jax's E dodge + R resists hard-counter your missing-HP P and W self-damage playstyle; you cannot out-DPS him past two items, so play for roams and picks elsewhere."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait E Counter Strike with a poke Q then walk out before you commit","Trade only in the 1-2s window right after his E ends","Roam and use E resets on ganks rather than dueling him straight"],"foe":["Land Counter Strike stun onto your dash-in and W all-in","Hit level 6 R to flip resists mid-trade","Drag every fight long so his stun and sustain win the extended DPS race"]},"early":"Jax bullies you from level 1 with Leap Strike range and the threat of E Counter Strike; his Q gap-close punishes any minion you try to last-hit up close, and you have no way to trade into an active E without feeding stun-empowered W damage.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are Jax's kingdom: with E up he wins every all-in, and your E Ashen Pursuit dash just walks you into the stun. Only trade in the sliver after Counter Strike expires, and never W-commit while he has E available.","late":"Post-6 R Grandmaster's Might gives Jax the resists and on-hit burst to survive your R Purgatory threshold and out-sustain your self-damaging W; you scale worse than him into items, so farm safe and win the map, not the 1v1.","whys":["Jax's Leap Strike range and E threat let him bully you at level 1.","Jax controls level 2 spacing; his Q punishes your last-hits up close.","Jax's E Counter Strike stun hard-punishes your level-3 dash-in commit.","Through 4-5 Jax wins every all-in whenever Counter Strike is available.","Jax's level-6 R flips resists and adds on-hit burst you can't race.","Jax's first item spike sharpens his stun-kill window while your burst fades.","Jax out-sustains your R and self-damage W in every extended late fight."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"jayce","win":["Jayce","Jayce","Jayce","Jayce","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Jayce dominates early with Hammer-form Q-E poke and ranged Shock Blast comboed through his Acceleration Gate; he chunks you from screens away and you have no gap-closer until E Ashen Pursuit at 3, so you bleed HP just walking to farm."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You spike hard: Jayce has no true ult, so his level 6 is a wet noodle while your R Purgatory totem gives a real execute. If you can survive to 6 with a health lead, your all-in with E dash-through and R flips the lane."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After first item your burst window opens: land Q Ritual Nails slow, E through him, and W Soul Ignition grey-health steroid to blow him up before his melee Hammer form can retaliate, using his missing-HP for your P Silver Stake."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late game reverts to Jayce's favour as a poke-and-reposition monster; if the game drags he shoves and pokes safely, so you must convert your item-timing kills into a snowball rather than scaling with him."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the poke phase to 6 without dying","Wait for his Cannon-Q cooldown then E-in for the all-in","Use missing-HP from his poke to fuel your P and R execute"],"foe":["Poke you down with Shock Blast through the Acceleration Gate","Keep the fight at range in Cannon form","Kite back into Hammer E knockback when you dash in"]},"early":"Jayce owns levels 1-4: his Cannon-form Q Shock Blast fired through the Acceleration Gate pokes you from max range, and his Hammer Q-E combo punishes any approach. You have no dash until 3 and no burst until items, so eat minimal poke and focus on not dying.","mid":"The lane inverts at 6. Jayce's ultimate is only a form-swap steroid, no burst spike, while your R Purgatory is a genuine execute totem. Hold your all-in for when his Cannon Q is down, E through him, and use his poke-inflicted missing HP to trigger P Silver Stake.","late":"With one item your assassin combo one-shots him inside melee range before Hammer form can knock you out, so item-timing is your kill window. But if the game goes long Jayce out-pokes and out-positions you, so cash your leads early instead of scaling.","whys":["Jayce out-ranges you at level 1 with Hammer poke and no risk.","Jayce's level-2 Q-E combo zones you off the wave.","Jayce keeps chunking you with ranged Shock Blast as you can't reach him.","Through 4-5 Jayce's poke advantage persists while you lack a burst spike.","Level 6 is even-to-yours: his ult is just a stance swap with no burst.","Your R Purgatory execute plus item burst gives you the all-in kill at 6.","Late reverts toward skill as Jayce's safe poke offsets your burst threat."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"karma","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Karma's early lane is her mantra'd Q Inner Flame; a RQ deals a burst plus AoE and her E shields and speeds her out of your dash range. Respect the mantra Q poke but note she has thin base defenses — if you dodge the skillshot the trade is even."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You spike clearly: Karma has no hard-CC ultimate and no escape beyond E, so once R Purgatory is online you can E Ashen Pursuit through her, Q Ritual Nails slow, and W burst her below your execute threshold before her shield out-values it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Karma's RE shield and RW root-DPS come online but she's still squishy; time your all-in when her Mantra is on cooldown, since without RE she can't shield-and-run your W Soul Ignition burst."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Karma becomes a utility enchanter with strong shields and speed for her team, so 1v1 she can peel your dash-in with RE and disengage; convert your mid-game kills before she out-utilities you in skirmishes."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge her Mantra-Q Inner Flame to keep trades even","All-in at 6 when her E/Mantra shield is down","Use E reset on her low base HP to snowball roams"],"foe":["Land mantra'd RQ poke and back off behind E speed","Shield your dash-in burst with RE and kite away","Use RW root to peel when you commit"]},"early":"Early lane is a skill test around Karma's Q Inner Flame: her mantra'd RQ chunks and her E shield-speed lets her disengage your approaches, but she's fragile and immobile beyond that. Dodge her skillshot Q and the poke war stays even through the first few levels.","mid":"Levels 3-5 remain even — she pokes with mantra Q, you look for a Q slow into E dash to trade, and whoever plays the Mantra cooldowns better wins the exchange. Don't force an all-in before 6; her E shield eats your uncharged burst.","late":"At 6 you take over: R Purgatory gives you a real execute Karma can't match, so E through her, slow with Q, and W her under the threshold while her Mantra is down. Later she pivots to enchanter utility and peels you with RE/RW, so bank your 6 spike into a lead before her shields scale.","whys":["Even at level 1: her Q poke trades against your farm, neither dominates.","Level 2 stays a skillshot duel around her Inner Flame.","Through level 3 her E shield offsets your new dash, keeping it even.","Levels 4-5 hinge on Mantra-cooldown play, no clear edge either way.","Level 6 stays even as her fresh shields answer your first R attempt.","Your first-item R Purgatory execute beats her non-CC ult and fragile body.","Late reverts to skill as her enchanter shields and speed peel your all-in."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"kassadin","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Kassadin"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kassadin is miserable early: his Q Null Sphere only shields against magic and he has no waveclear or trade tools before points in W, so you shove and poke freely. Land Q Ritual Nails slows and chunk him with W Soul Ignition — this is your window."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Riftwalk arrives and the lane flips: Kass can now blink onto you or escape your E Ashen Pursuit dash entirely. Your R Purgatory execute still threatens him, so 6-vs-6 is roughly even, but he stops being free."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After his first component (usually tear/lost chapter into Rod), Kass's Riftwalk cooldown and magic damage ramp; he starts winning short trades with RQ burst and you can no longer freely all-in through his Q shield."},{"when":"Late","text":"This is Kassadin's game — stacked Riftwalks let him blink-kill you or dodge your entire combo, and his magic shield eats your AP burst. If you didn't build a lead by 9, he out-scales and out-mobilities you hard."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove and all-in before level 6 while he's defenseless","Poke with Q slow + W before he has Riftwalk mobility","Deny his farm and roam to snowball off his weak early"],"foe":["Reach 6 and stack Riftwalk to blink your combo","Use Q Null Sphere shield to absorb your W burst","Scale to late where RQ burst kills you outright"]},"early":"Kassadin has no answer to you before 6: his Q Null Sphere is a magic-only shield, his early damage is nonexistent, and he can't clear waves. Shove hard, land Q Ritual Nails slows, and pile on W Soul Ignition damage — every level before his ult is yours to press.","mid":"At 6 Riftwalk changes everything: he can blink onto you or out of your E dash, so your free-kill phase ends. Your R Purgatory execute keeps the 6-vs-6 even, but respect that he's no longer a punching bag and can now disengage your all-ins.","late":"Post-first-item and beyond, Kassadin takes over — stacked Riftwalks let him blink-burst you with RQ or dodge your combo entirely while his magic shield soaks your damage. Force your advantage in the first six levels or he simply out-scales you.","whys":["Level 1 is even: his Q shield offsets your lack of a gap-closer yet.","Level 2 stays a skill trade — you poke, his Q absorbs magic burst.","Level 3 is even as his Null Sphere shield answers your fresh dash-in.","Levels 4-5 stay even, both waiting on power spikes at 6.","Level 6 is even: Riftwalk arrives but your R execute answers it.","First item stays even as his RQ burst rises against your fading edge.","Two-plus items: stacked Riftwalk and magic shield hand Kass the lane."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"kayle","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Kayle"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kayle is a helpless melee until level 6: no range, no waveclear, no escape. You can Q Ritual Nails slow, E Ashen Pursuit onto her and W Soul Ignition burst almost freely — but she's built to survive this, so kills matter more than trades that just make her back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Divine Judgment is a full-invulnerability ult that hard-counters your R Purgatory execute and W all-in; if she buys it, your combo bounces off the immunity window. Bait or wait it out — 6-vs-6 is even, not yours."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Kayle hits her first ranged form at level 6 and Nashor's/first-item spikes let her E on-hit poke you from distance; your assassin burst window shrinks as she starts kiting your dash-in."},{"when":"Late","text":"Full-form Kayle with waves and R invuln is a hyper-carry who out-ranges, out-DPSes, and out-survives you; this is entirely her game unless you converted the early levels into a decisive lead and ended fast."}],"wants":{"you":["Deny farm and dive her hard before level 6","Force her to burn R or back with repeated all-ins","Snowball a lead and close the game before she out-scales"],"foe":["Survive to 6 and 11 to unlock range and invuln","Use R Divine Judgment to negate your all-in and execute","Farm safely and out-scale into an unstoppable late"]},"early":"Kayle is one of the weakest lane champions before 6 — melee, no waveclear, no mobility — so the early skill test is purely whether you can convert that into real kills rather than just chip. Q slow, E in, W burst, and try to deny her farm, but know she's designed to weather this phase.","mid":"At 6 her R Divine Judgment invulnerability directly neutralizes your R Purgatory execute and W commit, so the all-in is even at best; time your burst for when her ult is down. Every level she gains ranged form and scaling, so your window is closing fast.","late":"Two-plus items into a full-form Kayle is a losing proposition: she kites your dash with ranged E on-hit, out-DPSes your burst, and R negates your execute. If you didn't snowball the early game and end, this matchup belongs to her.","whys":["Level 1 is even: she's weak but built to survive your chip.","Level 2 stays even — you press, she farms through it safely.","Level 3 is even as your dash-in only chips a champion made to endure it.","Levels 4-5 stay even; she scales toward 6 as your edge fails to convert.","Level 6 is even: her R invulnerability cancels your all-in and execute.","First item stays even as her ranged form starts kiting your burst.","Two-plus items: ranged DPS plus R invuln make late entirely Kayle's."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"kennen","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kennen out-ranges you and stacks Marks from safety with shurikens, so trading straight-up feeds his poke. Farm behind minions, only step in when his shuriken is on cooldown, and use Ritual Nails to whittle him rather than committing your blink into a stun."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Purgatory is your edge: Kennen has no sustain and burns his own energy poking, so once he dips you can dive with W speed and E through him for a guaranteed execute. Bait his Lightning Rush, then all-in when his stun and escape are spent — this is your best all-in window."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Kennen's first-item spike (Hextech/Liandry) lets him zone you and shred your grey health during W. Match with your own AP power spike and keep abusing his lack of sustain — a single good E reset onto him swings the trade hard in your favour."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights Kennen's R is a flanking AoE stun that can catch your dive. Play the fight as cleanup: let him commit R, then E in on low targets and use Purgatory to reset, but never facecheck his Slicing Maelstrom alone."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait his shuriken/Lightning Rush, then all-in on cooldown","Land Ritual Nails Marks to slow and chunk before you E","Use Purgatory + E resets to punish his no-sustain frame"],"foe":["Poke you down with shurikens and stack Marks from range","Land the full 3-Mark stun to lock your blink and burst you","Flank with Slicing Maelstrom to chain-stun your dive"]},"early":"Kennen wins the raw poke war, so respect his range and farm patiently — trade only when his shuriken is down and use Ritual Nails to punish his energy-hungry harass rather than walking into a Mark stun.","mid":"Your first-item AP and Purgatory tilt the mid-game your way. Kennen has no sustain, so bait his stun and Lightning Rush, then dive with W speed and E through him for the execute; a takedown resets your E to escape or chain.","late":"Teamfights hinge on his R. Stay out of Slicing Maelstrom range, let him blow his flank, then clean up low targets with E + Purgatory resets. Don't facecheck him solo — his AoE stun turns a dive into a death.","whys":["Kennen's shuriken range and Mark poke beat your melee trades at levels 3-5, so it's a skill matchup on patience.","Kennen keeps out-poking you at 4-5; playing around his cooldowns keeps it even rather than losing.","Even farming, careful positioning around his shurikens keeps the lane balanced through the pre-6 window.","Neither side commits fully before 5 — respecting his stun keeps trades neutral.","At 6 raw stats are even, but the all-in tools tilt on execution — skill decides who wins the first fight.","Purgatory plus your dive threat punishes Kennen's total lack of sustain, giving Locke the clear level-6 all-in edge.","Late-game his teamfight R matches your pick potential, so the matchup stays a skill test into the fight phase."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"kled","win":["Kled","Kled","Kled","Kled","Kled","Kled","Kled"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Kled's Q Bear Trap on a Rope pulls him onto you and applies a heavy DoT/slow; comboed with W Violent Tendencies attack-speed steroid he shreds you in a short trade. His E Jousting dash also dodges your E Ashen Pursuit angle, so every all-in favours him."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Chaaaaaaaarge!!! gives Kled an engage speed boost and a mounted health bar, so even landing R Purgatory he re-mounts through your execute threshold and out-sustains your W self-damage in the extended fight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"A first Trinity/BORK spike turns Kled's W on-hit into a DPS wall your burst can't race; his Skaarl HP pool acts like a second life bar that eats your combo before you can execute."},{"when":"Late","text":"Kled scales as a durable bruiser with two health bars and re-mount sustain; your assassin burst falls off against his effective HP, so avoid the 1v1 and use E resets to impact other lanes instead."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge his Q Bear Trap pull to deny the all-in","Trade only when his W Violent Tendencies is on cooldown","Roam with E resets rather than dueling his two health bars"],"foe":["Land Q pull to lock you into a W attack-speed shred","Re-mount Skaarl to survive your R execute threshold","Drag fights long so his sustain and HP pool win"]},"early":"Kled bullies you from level 1: his Q Bear Trap on a Rope is a long-range pull that yanks him onto you with a damaging slow, and his passive Skaarl gives him a second health bar you have to chew through. You can't out-trade that, so respect his Q range and give up the early aggression.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Kled's: W Violent Tendencies shreds you in any extended trade, E Jousting dodges your dash angle, and at 6 his R re-mount lets him survive your R Purgatory execute and out-sustain your self-damaging W. Never all-in into an active W.","late":"Into items Kled's Skaarl HP pool plus re-mount sustain acts as a wall your burst can't break; he out-durabilities your assassin damage and wins every drawn-out fight. Farm safe, avoid the duel, and use your E resets to matter elsewhere on the map.","whys":["Kled's level-1 Q pull and Skaarl second health bar bully you outright.","Kled controls level 2 with Q range and W attack-speed trades.","Kled's W shred and E dash-dodge win the level-3 all-in.","Through 4-5 Kled out-trades you with W steroid and two health bars.","Kled's level-6 R re-mount survives your execute and out-sustains your W.","Kled's first-item on-hit spike walls your burst behind his HP pool.","Kled's two health bars and re-mount sustain win every late fight."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"ksante","win":["Locke","Locke","Locke","Locke","Locke","Locke","Locke"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Stack Ritual Nails marks and let Silver Stake chew his oversized HP bar; K'Sante's early All Out damage is soft and his W stun is telegraphed, so you win extended pokes."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Purgatory ignores his effective-HP tankiness once he drops below the threshold, and if he pops R to go All Out he sheds resistances and armor plating, making him far easier to burst."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first AP item plus Silver Stake missing-HP scaling races ahead of a bruiser first item; you can Ashen Pursuit through his Ntofo Strikes to dodge the pull-stun and reset on the kill."},{"when":"Late","text":"He never solo-kills you and your execute totem cleans up any All Out dash-in; group with R zoning and he becomes a stat-check you keep winning."}],"wants":{"you":["Space so his Ntofo Strikes (Q) stack never lands the pull-stun","Let Silver Stake and W grey-health erode his fat HP bar over trades","Bait his R (All Out) then punish the lost resistances with Purgatory"],"foe":["Land the second Ntofo Strike to pull-stun you into a wall","Peel your Ashen Pursuit blink with his W dash-and-stun","Survive to All Out and dash you under his tower"]},"early":"You own the early lane. Ritual Nails marks plus Silver Stake's missing-HP on-hit shred a health pool this large, and K'Sante's level 1-2 damage is negligible while his W stun is slow and dodgeable. Keep your distance from the second Ntofo Strike, poke on cooldowns, and you dictate every trade.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay firmly yours. Your mark stacks and grey-health steroid keep whittling him faster than he can sustain, and Ashen Pursuit lets you weave in and out of his Ntofo range without eating the pull-stun. At 6 Purgatory answers his tankiness directly, and baiting All Out strips his resistances for the kill.","late":"Even into items you stay ahead. Silver Stake's percent-missing scaling means his effective-HP stacking never saves him, and Purgatory executes through any All Out engage. He can't solo-kill you, so this is a lane you snowball and carry.","whys":["Silver Stake and Ritual Nails punish his huge HP bar while his level-1 damage is nil.","Your marks keep out-trading a K'Sante whose early All Out is weak.","Grey-health W trades erode him faster than he sustains at level 3.","You out-DPS his tankiness through 4-5 and dodge the pull-stun with E.","Purgatory ignores effective HP and punishes his stripped resistances in All Out.","Your AP spike plus missing-HP on-hit beats his bruiser first item.","Percent-execute scaling means his HP stacking never lets him escape you late."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"lillia","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Lillia wants to kite with Q (Blooming Blows) and Seed poke while dodging your marks; whoever spaces better wins, so land Ritual Nails to slow her before she stacks passive burn on you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Purgatory hard-counters her escape — she can't Dream Dust her way out of an execute totem, and Ashen Pursuit closes the gap her E can't outrun once she's low."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even fight, but Silver Stake's missing-HP damage races her passive DoT; commit before her R (Lullaby) sleep comes back up so she can't reset the trade."},{"when":"Late","text":"She scales into a teamfight sleep-bot; pick her before Lullaby lands and your burst plus execute deletes a squishy she has no armor to hide behind."}],"wants":{"you":["Slow her with Ritual Nails so she can't kite your marks","Save Ashen Pursuit to close her Q (Blooming Blows) disengage","Commit at 6 where Purgatory beats her escape and sustain"],"foe":["Kite with Blooming Blows and stack passive burn from range","Poke you down with W (Watch Out!) seeds before you engage","Land Lullaby (R) sleep to reset a losing trade"]},"early":"A skill-matchup early. Lillia is slippery — Blooming Blows lets her dance around your Ritual Nails and her passive burn adds up if you chase blindly. Land your mark to slow her, farm safely, and don't overextend into her seed poke. Neither of you kills the other at level 1-2, so respect spacing.","mid":"Through 3-5 it stays even and about execution. She kites, you punish whiffed seeds with mark stacks and grey-health trades. The swing comes at 6: Purgatory gives you a kill button she can't escape, and Ashen Pursuit blinks past her Q disengage to finish. Bait her Lullaby before you fully commit.","late":"Post-items it evens out again on paper, but your assassin profile favors the pick. Silver Stake shreds her low-HP frame and Purgatory executes through her sustain. Catch her before Lullaby is up and she folds; let her land the AoE sleep and she resets — so play around that one cooldown.","whys":["Even level 1 — she kites with Blooming Blows, you slow with marks, no kill.","Skill spacing decides level 2; neither has a reliable kill threat.","Her kite versus your mark punish stays even through level 3.","Level 4-5 remains a spacing duel with no clear favorite.","Still even before ults — her poke trades against your grey-health.","Purgatory hands you a kill button her escape and sustain can't answer.","Post-items evens out as her teamfight sleep scaling matches your pick threat."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"lucian","win":["Lucian","Lucian","Lucian","Lucian","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Lucian bullies you with Piercing Light (Q) poke and Relentless Pursuit (E) dash-cancels; his double-shot passive and range mean he wins the pre-6 poke war, so farm defensively and dodge his Q line."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your swing point — Purgatory executes a squishy marksman with no defensive layers, and Ashen Pursuit blinks onto him before he can E away; commit here to flip the lane."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even trade window; Silver Stake's missing-HP on-hit plus your burst races his Culling, but respect his second E and Relentless dash to disengage."},{"when":"Late","text":"He out-ranges and out-DPSes you in a straight fight, so play for the pick — flank with E and open on Purgatory before he can kite; a whiffed dash means he's dead."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the poke phase and hit 6 with health to commit","Blink with Ashen Pursuit past his Relentless Pursuit (E) dash","Open Purgatory on him before he can kite or Culling you"],"foe":["Poke you down with Piercing Light and passive double-shots","Space with his range so your marks never stack","Save Relentless Pursuit (E) to dash out of your all-in"]},"early":"Lucian owns the early lane. His Piercing Light poke, passive double-shot, and superior range let him chip you every time you go for a last hit, and his E cancels your attempts to trade back. Take the safe CS, dodge his Q lines, and don't feed the poke — you're playing to survive to your spike, not to win level 1-2.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay his: he has the dash-cancel tempo and the range to keep you at mark distance. But at 6 everything flips. Purgatory is a clean execute on a marksman with zero defensive stats, and Ashen Pursuit lets you gap-close through his Relentless Pursuit. Commit the instant your ult is up and you have him.","late":"In a straight fight late he out-ranges and out-DPSes you, so don't stand and trade. Play the assassin: flank, blink in with E, and open Purgatory before he can kite or fire Culling. If he burns his E wrong he's dead; if he saves it, disengage and wait for the next pick.","whys":["Lucian's range, poke, and passive double-shot beat you at level 1.","His Piercing Light and E tempo out-trade you through level 2.","He keeps mark distance and bullies your CS at level 3.","His range and dash-cancels still control the lane at 4-5.","At 6 it evens — your execute answers his squishiness against his kite.","Purgatory cleanly executes a defenseless marksman once you gap-close.","Post-items evens out — his DPS in a fight versus your pick threat off E."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"malphite","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Malphite","Skill","Malphite","Malphite"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early it's a spacing game — dodge Seismic Shard (Q) slows and stack marks, but once he puts points in W (Thunderclap) and buys armor his passive shield eats your Silver Stake pokes."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Danger point: Unstoppable Force (R) is a point-and-click knock-up your Ashen Pursuit can't dodge on reaction, so respect his all-in and don't stand in Q range with R up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"His armor spike stacks with his passive shield to blunt your on-hit and AP burst; you can still burn his shield with W grey-health but he out-sustains your poke now."},{"when":"Late","text":"Malphite becomes an armor wall with a game-changing R; Purgatory still executes him low but landing it through his shield and tankiness is hard, so play around his ult, not raw damage."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke and stack marks before his armor and passive shield come online","Dodge or bait Seismic Shard (Q) to close and trade freely","Save mobility for after his Unstoppable Force (R) so it can't cancel you"],"foe":["Buy armor early so his passive shield negates your Silver Stake pokes","Land Seismic Shard slow to set up Thunderclap trades","Flatten you with point-and-click Unstoppable Force (R)"]},"early":"A skill lane at level 1-3. Malphite's passive shield and Q slow make poke awkward, but before he itemizes armor your Ritual Nails marks and Silver Stake still bite. Dodge Seismic Shard, stack marks when his shield is down, and don't let him chunk you with a Q-into-Thunderclap combo. Neither snowballs the other yet.","mid":"The tide turns at level 4-5 as his W and first armor make his shield near-constant, blunting your burst. Level 6 evens back out as your Purgatory execute answers his all-in: Unstoppable Force is an unmissable knock-up that Ashen Pursuit cannot dodge on reaction, so track his R, but if he burns it you can flip and finish. Bait or count his ult before you commit anything.","late":"With items Malphite is an armor wall that shrugs off on-hit and AP alike, and his R swings fights. Purgatory can still execute him once he's genuinely low, but forcing him there through the shield is hard. Play around his ultimate timer and pick your spots — don't try to stat-check the mountain.","whys":["Even early — his shield and Q slow trade against your marks, no kill.","Skill spacing still decides level 2 before his armor comes online.","Neither champ kills the other at level 3; it stays a poke duel.","His W plus first armor and passive shield start blunting your burst at 4-5.","Level 6 evens out — his unmissable R danger against your execute potential.","His armor and shield out-sustain your on-hit poke after first item.","Late he's an armor wall with a fight-swinging R your burst can't out-race."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"maokai","win":["Maokai","Maokai","Maokai","Maokai","Skill","Skill","Maokai"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Maokai out-sustains you hard — his passive heals off spells and Sapling Toss (W... E) pokes you for free while regenerating; his Q (Bramble Smash) knockback zones your marks, so trading is a losing battle early."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Slight relief window — Purgatory can execute him if you burst through the sustain, but Nature's Grasp (R) roots you from screen-away and his heal keeps him topped, so it stays even at best."},{"when":"1st item","text":"It levels off here — your first AP item plus Silver Stake missing-HP finally trade even against his sustain and tankiness, so you hold your own though neither solo-kills."},{"when":"Late","text":"Maokai becomes an unkillable rooting tank; you can't solo him, so play for roam and let your execute totem contribute in teamfights rather than lane."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Sapling Toss (E) poke so his passive doesn't free-heal","Burst hard enough at 6 that Purgatory outruns his regen","Roam and farm rather than trade into his sustain"],"foe":["Free-heal off his passive while poking with saplings","Knock you out of mark range with Bramble Smash (Q)","Root you from off-screen with Nature's Grasp (R)"]},"early":"Maokai wins the early lane through sheer sustain. His passive heals him every time he casts, Sapling Toss pokes you for nothing, and Bramble Smash knocks you out of Ritual Nails range whenever you try to trade. You simply can't out-poke a champ that regenerates for free — take safe CS, dodge saplings, and accept you're behind on the trade math.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay his for the same reasons: your grey-health trades get healed off and his knockback denies your mark stacking. At 6 you get a small window — if you can burst him low, Purgatory executes through the sustain — but Nature's Grasp roots you from range and his heal usually keeps him above threshold. Treat 6 as even, not a kill.","late":"With items Maokai is an unkillable tank who roots you out of any escape. Your on-hit and burst can't overcome his regen and health, so stop trying to solo him. Roam for plays, farm your side, and save your execute for teamfights where Purgatory finishes targets his frontline can't protect.","whys":["His passive heal and sapling poke beat your marks at level 1.","Free sustain plus Bramble Smash knockback out-trade you at level 2.","His regen erases your grey-health trades through level 3.","Sustain and knockback keep the lane his at 4-5.","Level 6 evens — your execute threat offsets his heal and long-range root.","First item evens it — your AP spike and missing-HP on-hit trade level with his sustain.","Late he's an unkillable rooting tank your burst can't out-race."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"mel","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Mel pokes with Radiant Volley and stacks Overwhelm on you from range; whoever spaces cleaner wins, so slow her with Ritual Nails and dodge her missiles before her passive detonation chunks you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your window — Purgatory executes a squishy mage who has no defensive layers, and Ashen Pursuit blinks past her Rebuttal (W) reflect timing if you bait it first; commit when your totem is up."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even trade — Silver Stake missing-HP races her burst, but respect Rebuttal: don't dump your combo into the reflect shield or you eat your own damage back."},{"when":"Late","text":"She's a squishy backline mage; play the assassin, flank with E and open Purgatory before Rebuttal is up, and she has nothing to survive your all-in."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait Rebuttal (W) before committing your burst combo","Slow her with Ritual Nails so she can't kite your marks","Open Purgatory at 6 on a mage with no defensive stats"],"foe":["Poke with Radiant Volley and detonate Overwhelm stacks","Reflect your engage with Rebuttal (W) to punish your dive","Space with range so your marks never stack up"]},"early":"A skill matchup early. Mel is a ranged mage who wants to chip you with Radiant Volley and build Overwhelm stacks for a passive detonation, so don't walk into her poke greedily. Land Ritual Nails to slow and control the space, dodge her missiles, and farm even. Neither of you kills the other at level 1-2 if you respect range.","mid":"Through 3-5 it stays even and about execution — her poke versus your mark punishes on whiffs. The lane swings at 6: Purgatory is a clean execute on a mage with zero defensive stats, and Ashen Pursuit closes the gap. The one trap is Rebuttal — bait the reflect before you commit, or your own burst comes back at you.","late":"Post-items it evens on paper but the pick favors you. Mel is squishy backline with no escape and only Rebuttal for defense. Flank, blink in with E, wait out or bait the reflect, then open Purgatory — she folds to a clean all-in every time you catch her cooldown down.","whys":["Even level 1 — her ranged poke trades against your marks and slow.","Skill spacing decides level 2; neither has a kill threat yet.","Her poke versus your mark punish stays even through level 3.","Level 4-5 remains a spacing duel with no clear favorite.","Still even before ults — her Overwhelm poke against your grey-health.","Purgatory cleanly executes a defenseless mage once you gap-close at 6.","Post-items evens out — her burst against your pick threat off E."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"mordekaiser","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Morde wants to land Q (Obliterate) into a full W (Indestructible) shield trade while his passive DoT ramps; dodge his Q and stack marks from range so his shield never tops off — clean spacing keeps it even."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your swing — bait or survive Realm of Death (R), and Purgatory executes him inside the death realm where no ally can help; Ashen Pursuit repositions in the 1v1 he forces."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even fight — Silver Stake missing-HP races his shield-sustain trades, but never dump your combo while Indestructible is up or you feed his heal."},{"when":"Late","text":"His R is a guaranteed 1v1 isolation; that actually suits you — inside the realm Purgatory finishes him and he can't Ghost your carry if he's dead, so win the duel he starts."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Obliterate (Q) so his shield trade never lands clean","Fight after Indestructible (W) shield expires, not during it","Win the isolated 1v1 his R forces and execute with Purgatory"],"foe":["Land Q into a full W shield to win the extended trade","Ramp passive DoT stacks while you're in melee range","Isolate you with Realm of Death (R) to steal your stats"]},"early":"A skill lane at level 1-3. Mordekaiser's game is landing Obliterate into an Indestructible shield to win a prolonged trade while his passive burn ramps. Deny that: dodge the Q, poke with marks from outside his shield window, and don't stand in melee feeding his DoT. Trade on your terms and it stays dead even.","mid":"Levels 3-5 remain a spacing duel — his shield trades against your grey-health and mark stacks, roughly even. Level 6 is your window. Realm of Death forces a 1v1 with no jungler help, which suits an assassin: bait or eat the R, then Purgatory executes him inside the realm. Ashen Pursuit lets you reposition through his slow.","late":"With items his R isolation is scary against most, but it plays into your hands — a clean 1v1 is exactly where Silver Stake and Purgatory shine, and he can't reflect an execute. Fight after his Indestructible drops, open your combo, and finish inside the death realm. Win the duel he starts and he has nothing left.","whys":["Even level 1 — his shield trade against your mark poke, no kill.","Skill spacing decides level 2; deny his Q-into-shield combo.","His DoT ramp versus your mark stacks stays even at level 3.","Level 4-5 remains a spacing duel with no clear favorite.","Still even before ults — his shield sustain against your grey-health.","Purgatory executes him inside his own R isolation at 6.","Post-items evens out — his shield trades against your duel-and-execute threat."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"nasus","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Nasus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Every time Nasus last-hits with Siphoning Strike (Q) he permanently grows; deny CS by trading into him whenever he winds up a stack, since your Ritual Nails (Q) marks let you punish the animation."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Nasus 6 gives Fury of the Sands, a bulk-and-damage aura, but your Purgatory (R) execute cares about his current HP not his armor, so a burst-and-totem all-in still works if he over-extends."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first-item power lets you keep poking the missing-HP Silver Stake (P) on him, but a stacked Nasus starts one-shotting minions and shoving you off XP."},{"when":"Late","text":"Nasus wins here: a big stack count plus Wither (E) cripples your attack speed and movement, so his Q chunks through your grey-health and out-scales your kit."}],"wants":{"you":["Punish his Q last-hit animations with marked trades","Roam and get plated turret gold before he scales","Buy early MR/health to survive Wither burst"],"foe":["Free-farm Siphoning Strike stacks uncontested","Land Wither to kite your E dashes and all-in","Drag the game to two-item Titanic/Sunfire territory"]},"early":"L1-2 is even skill: Nasus is a pure scaling stat-check with no early kill pressure, so you contest CS freely with Ritual Nails (Q) marks and Silver Stake (P) chip while he tries only to stack.","mid":"Through L3-6 it stays a skill matchup because Wither (E) is his only combat tool and it is a long cooldown; dodge or bait it and your Ashen Pursuit (E) blink still lets you dictate trades and deny stacks.","late":"By 2+ items Nasus takes over: a heavy stack count plus Wither slows your grey-health steroid and attack speed to a crawl, and his sustained Q outpaces your assassin burst window.","whys":["Nasus has zero level-1 threat and only wants to stack, so it is purely skill.","Level 2 is still an even farming lane with no Nasus kill pattern.","At level 3 his only tool is Wither, which you can dodge, keeping it skill.","Levels 4-5 remain skill as you trade marks against his stacking animations.","Level 6 Fury of the Sands adds bulk but no lane-ending threat, still skill.","First item is even because your poke offsets his early stack lead.","By two items Nasus's stacked Q plus Wither out-scales and out-slows you."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"nautilus","win":["Nautilus","Nautilus","Nautilus","Nautilus","Skill","Skill","Nautilus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Nautilus's Dredge Line (Q) hook plus Titan's Wrath (W) shield and the Staggering Blow (P) root make every trade lopsided; his passive roots you on the first auto so your Ashen Pursuit (E) dash can be caught mid-animation."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Level 6 evens out: your Purgatory (R) execute threatens to finish him after his W shield pops, and you burst faster than his tanky kit expects, so a clean all-in below his HP threshold can flip a gank."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still roughly even at one item; you can dodge Dredge Line (Q) and use the cooldown window to poke Silver Stake (P), but one hooked-in point-and-click Depth Charge (R) still chains all his CC."},{"when":"Late","text":"Nautilus scales as an unkillable CC-bot: Depth Charge (R) knockup plus Q hook plus passive root lock you out of your reset windows and he simply builds full tank."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Dredge Line then punish the long cooldown","Save Purgatory to execute after his W shield fades","Sidestep so his passive root never lands first"],"foe":["Land Q hook into passive root for a free trade","Chain Depth Charge R into your dash animation","Build full tank and become an unkillable peel bot"]},"early":"L1-2 favours Nautilus: his Staggering Blow (P) roots you on the first basic attack and Titan's Wrath (W) shield eats your poke, so he wins any short trade and you cannot commit Ashen Pursuit (E) safely.","mid":"Through L3-6 Nautilus keeps the edge with Dredge Line (Q) hook plus W shield, until your level-6 Purgatory (R) execute finally gives you an all-in answer once his shield is down.","late":"By 2+ items Nautilus is a full-tank CC machine: Depth Charge (R) plus Q plus passive lock you down through your grey-health steroid and deny the E reset chains your assassin pattern relies on.","whys":["Level 1 Nautilus roots you with his passive on the first auto, favouring him.","Level 2 his W shield and root still win every short trade.","At level 3 Dredge Line hook adds hard engage in his favour.","Levels 4-5 his shield uptime and CC keep the trades lopsided.","Level 6 evens out because your Purgatory execute threatens him after W fades.","First item stays skill as you dodge Q and trade in its cooldown window.","Late, full-tank Nautilus chains CC and out-scales your burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"neeko","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Neeko pokes with Tangle-Barbs (Q) and Shapesplitter (W) clone auto-resets, but her CC comes only off a landed Q root; sidestep it and your Ritual Nails (Q) marks plus Silver Stake (P) chip win the sustained trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Locke spikes hard here: Neeko's Pop Blossom (R) needs a wind-up channel, and your Purgatory (R) totem plus Ashen Pursuit (E) blink let you burst her below the execute threshold before her ult detonates."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even at one item; you can all-in when her Q is down, but her clone (W) baits your Purgatory placement and a hidden Pop Blossom (R) can catch a greedy dash."},{"when":"Late","text":"Skill matchup late: she is squishy so your execute always threatens her, but a fed Neeko landing Q-root into full Pop Blossom (R) can one-shot back, so respect her burst windows."}],"wants":{"you":["Sidestep Tangle-Barbs to open a free marked trade","All-in at 6 before Pop Blossom finishes channeling","Track her clone so it never baits your Purgatory"],"foe":["Land Q root to set up Pop Blossom burst","Use Shapesplitter clone to dodge your execute","Poke you down with W-reset autos and Q from range"]},"early":"L1-2 is even skill: Neeko's only threat is a landed Tangle-Barbs (Q), so sidestep it and your Silver Stake (P) missing-HP chip plus Ashen Pursuit (E) mobility keep the farm lane neutral.","mid":"Through L3-6 it stays skill until your level-6 spike, where Purgatory (R) and your burst can execute her mid Pop Blossom (R) channel before it goes off, giving Locke the clear kill turn.","late":"By 2+ items it settles back to skill: she stays squishy so your totem always threatens a finish, but a fed Neeko can Q-root into full ult and burst you first, so the lane is decided by who lands the opener.","whys":["Level 1 is even because Neeko's only threat is a dodgeable Q root.","Level 2 stays skill as marked trades answer her poke.","At level 3 her CC is still gated behind landing Tangle-Barbs, keeping it even.","Levels 4-5 remain skill with both trading pre-ult.","Level 6 favours Locke: you can execute her through the Pop Blossom channel.","First item is even as both sides threaten burst on a landed spell.","Late stays skill since both are squishy and decided by the opener."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"olaf","win":["Olaf","Olaf","Olaf","Olaf","Olaf","Olaf","Olaf"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Olaf's Undertow (Q) axe slows hard and Reckless Swing (E) true-damages through your grey-health; his Vicious Strikes (W) lifesteal steroid means he out-sustains and out-trades you at every level if he picks up the axe."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Ragnarok (R) makes Olaf immune to your slows and CC and gives armor, so your kite-and-execute plan collapses; he walks through Ritual Nails (Q) and your Purgatory (R) execute can't stop his commit."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Olaf's early bruiser items plus W lifesteal let him tank your burst and E true-damage you down; you cannot win a straight all-in and must farm cautiously."},{"when":"Late","text":"Olaf still favours: Ragnarok (R) unstoppable dive plus E true damage ignores your squishy assassin build, and his Q slow catches your Ashen Pursuit (E) resets."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge the Undertow axe so you aren't slowed into E","Play for roams and side-lane pressure, not the 1v1","Bait Ragnarok early then disengage with your blink"],"foe":["Land Q axe to slow you into Reckless Swing range","Pop Ragnarok to ignore your slows and totem CC","Sustain through your poke with W lifesteal and all-in"]},"early":"L1-2 favours Olaf: even before axe pickup his base damage and Vicious Strikes (W) sustain beat your poke, and a landed Undertow (Q) sets up a Reckless Swing (E) true-damage trade you can't answer.","mid":"Through L3-6 Olaf stays ahead; his Q-slow-into-E combo and W lifesteal grind you down, and at 6 Ragnarok (R) makes him immune to your slows and CC, removing your only kiting tools.","late":"By 2+ items Olaf still wins the 1v1: Ragnarok (R) unstoppable engage plus Reckless Swing (E) true damage tears through your squishy build, so your value comes from roaming and objectives, not dueling him.","whys":["Level 1 Olaf out-damages and out-sustains your poke, favouring him.","Level 2 his base kit and W lifesteal keep trades in his favour.","At level 3 Q-slow into E true damage locks in his edge.","Levels 4-5 his sustain and axe pressure keep you on the back foot.","Level 6 Ragnarok removes your slows and CC, strongly favouring him.","First item his bruiser sustain tanks your burst and E chunks you.","Late, unstoppable Ragnarok plus true damage beats your squishy build."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"ornn","win":["Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn","Ornn"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ornn's Bellows Breath (W) shield eats your poke and makes him brittle-immune while it's up, and Searing Charge (E) knocks you up into a Q brittle-detonate; his tankiness shrugs off your early Silver Stake (P) chip."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Call of the Forge God (R) is a huge knockup and slow that catches your Ashen Pursuit (E) dashes, and his brittle passive amplifies all his CC; your Purgatory (R) execute rarely gets him low enough to matter."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Ornn free-upgrades his items and builds pure tank, so your assassin burst plinks off his HP while a single E-Q brittle combo chunks your grey-health."},{"when":"Late","text":"Ornn scales into an unkillable frontline: double R knockups plus brittle CC lock you out of every reset window and his items out-value yours for free."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Searing Charge so you avoid the brittle knockup","Poke only when his Bellows Breath shield is down","Roam for plates and side pressure over the 1v1"],"foe":["Land E-Q brittle combo for a heavy CC trade","Shield your trades with Bellows Breath and out-tank you","Scale to free-upgraded full-tank with double R knockups"]},"early":"L1-2 favours Ornn: Bellows Breath (W) shields through your poke and his base tankiness means your Silver Stake (P) missing-HP chip barely registers while he zones you off CS.","mid":"Through L3-6 Ornn keeps control; Searing Charge (E) into Q brittle-detonate is a hard CC trade you can't match, and at 6 Call of the Forge God (R) catches your Ashen Pursuit (E) blink for a full knockup combo.","late":"By 2+ items Ornn is an unkillable, free-upgraded frontline: your squishy burst can't punch through his HP, and his double-R knockups plus brittle amplification deny the reset chains your kit needs.","whys":["Level 1 Ornn's tankiness shrugs your poke, favouring him.","Level 2 his base bulk and W shield keep the lane in his favour.","At level 3 E-Q brittle combo gives him a hard CC trade edge.","Levels 4-5 his shield uptime and CC keep you zoned.","Level 6 Call of the Forge God catches your dashes, strongly his.","First item free-upgrades and tankiness blunt your burst.","Late, unkillable Ornn out-scales and CC-locks your assassin pattern."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"pantheon","win":["Pantheon","Pantheon","Pantheon","Pantheon","Pantheon","Pantheon","Pantheon"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Pantheon's Comet Spear (Q) poke and Shield Vault (W) stun-gap close the moment you step up, and his Aegis Assault (E) block negates your all-in damage; his early kill pressure is brutal on a squishy assassin."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Grand Starfall (R) gives him global roam and dive pressure, and point-blank he combos W-stun into Q for a burst that beats your Purgatory (R) execute window before you can retaliate."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Pantheon's early-game item spike keeps him ahead; his W stun sets up a full combo through your grey-health, and E blocks the auto damage your Silver Stake (P) relies on."},{"when":"Late","text":"Pantheon falls off relatively but still favours the 1v1 into you: his W-stun-into-burst opener and E block let him win the short trade before your reset chains get going."}],"wants":{"you":["Respect the W stun range and don't walk into poke","Wait out Aegis Assault before committing burst","Farm safe and scale past his early-game window"],"foe":["Land Comet Spear poke to chip you pre-all-in","Open with W stun into Q for a burst kill","Block your damage with Aegis Assault then re-engage"]},"early":"L1-2 favours Pantheon: Comet Spear (Q) out-ranges your poke and a level-2 Shield Vault (W) stun into Q burst can nearly kill you before your Ashen Pursuit (E) is even up.","mid":"Through L3-6 Pantheon dominates; his W-stun-into-Q combo and Aegis Assault (E) block beat your all-in, and at 6 Grand Starfall (R) adds dive and roam pressure you can't match.","late":"By 2+ items Pantheon cools off but still wins the isolated trade into you: his stun opener and E damage-block let him burst you before your Purgatory (R) execute and E resets come online.","whys":["Level 1 Pantheon out-pokes and threatens a fast all-in, favouring him.","Level 2 his W stun into Q nearly kills you, clearly his.","At level 3 his combo plus E block beats your trade attempts.","Levels 4-5 his kill pressure and poke keep you suppressed.","Level 6 Grand Starfall adds dive and roam threat in his favour.","First item his early spike sustains the lead over your burst.","Late, his stun-burst opener still wins the short trade into you."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"poppy","win":["Poppy","Poppy","Poppy","Poppy","Skill","Skill","Poppy"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Poppy's Hammer Shock (Q) chunks and Steadfast Presence (W) passively negates your Ashen Pursuit (E) dash while active, and Heroic Charge (E) into a wall stuns you; her anti-dash kit directly counters your mobility."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"It evens at 6: Keeper's Verdict (R) is her only real ult threat but it's a wind-up, and if she uses W's dash-block you can bait it, then your Purgatory (R) execute finally gives you a kill turn."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Roughly even; you can poke Silver Stake (P) when her Q is down, but her W still eats your E engage and E-into-wall stun sets up her burst, so trades stay a coin-flip."},{"when":"Late","text":"Poppy pulls ahead again: tanky W permanently shuts off your dash resets and her E-wall stun plus R displacement deny the reset chains your assassin pattern depends on."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait Steadfast Presence before using your E dash","All-in at 6 when her W is on cooldown","Poke with Silver Stake while Hammer Shock is down"],"foe":["Keep W up to negate your Ashen Pursuit dash","Land E into a wall for a stun-into-burst trade","Build tanky and deny your reset chains all game"]},"early":"L1-2 favours Poppy: Hammer Shock (Q) out-trades your poke and Steadfast Presence (W) can grounding-negate your Ashen Pursuit (E), so your main mobility tool is unreliable and she wins the short trade.","mid":"Through L3-5 Poppy keeps the edge with her Q chunk and E-into-wall stun, but at level 6 it evens out because your Purgatory (R) execute and burst give you a real kill turn once you bait her W dash-block.","late":"By 2+ items Poppy tilts it back in her favour: a tanky Steadfast Presence (W) permanently disables your dash resets and her E-wall stun plus Keeper's Verdict (R) lock down the reset chains your kit relies on.","whys":["Level 1 Poppy's Q and W dash-negation win the trade, favouring her.","Level 2 her poke and anti-mobility keep the edge hers.","At level 3 Hammer Shock plus E-wall stun beat your trades.","Levels 4-5 her chunk and stun setup stay in her favour.","Level 6 evens out as Purgatory gives you a kill turn once W is baited.","First item stays skill as both trade around Q and W cooldowns.","Late, tanky Poppy's W and stun deny your reset-driven pattern."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"quinn","win":["Quinn","Quinn","Quinn","Quinn","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Quinn's Blinding Assault (Q) plus Vault (E) reset is a full trade she wins outright; every time she lands Q your auto-heavy Silver Stake pressure is neutered, so respect her cooldowns and only walk up when Q is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"At 6 you finally have Purgatory (R): after any Q-slow or W-primed burst you can drop the totem and execute her below the growing threshold before Skystrike lets her kite, flipping the lane in your favour."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you finish your first AP item your W grey-health steroid plus E reset lets you all-in through her E knockback, but she can Valor-mount (R) to disengage, so blow it only when she has used R or lacks flash."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late she roams and splits with Behind Enemy Lines; if she gets ahead early her ranged poke snowballs, so the game hinges on whether your 6 window closed the early deficit."}],"wants":{"you":["Q Ritual Nails marks landed so your slow sets up E gap-close","level 6 so Purgatory can execute after her Vault","W grey-health active before you commit the all-in"],"foe":["Blinding Assault (Q) landed to blind your on-hit autos","open ground to kite you with Vault knockback and Heightened Senses MS","picks and roams via Behind Enemy Lines to snowball elsewhere"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 Quinn owns the lane: her Blinding Assault (Q) outranges everything you have and the blind shuts off your Silver Stake on-hit, while Harrier auto-marks let her chunk you for free whenever you go for CS. Do not try to trade through Q up; farm at max range and dodge the telegraphed skillshot.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay dangerous until your ultimate. Her Vault (E) is a targeted dash-and-reset that hops over you, resetting her Q for a second blind, so most of this window she out-trades you. The moment you hit 6, Purgatory changes the math: bait her Q or E, then Q-slow into E to close and totem-execute her below threshold.","late":"After your first item the lane is a coinflip skill matchup — your W steroid plus E-reset burst can delete her if she mispositions, but Valor (R) and Skystrike knockback give her a hard disengage. She out-scales into a roaming split threat, so you want to have already cracked her tempo during your level-6 spike.","whys":["Quinn's level-1 Q outranges you and the blind shuts off your Silver Stake autos.","At 2 Harrier marks and Q poke chunk you every time you step up to farm.","Level 3 Vault gives her a dash-reset and a second blind that wins the trade.","Levels 4-5 her Q-E cooldowns stay ahead of your gap-close, so she keeps kiting.","At 5 it evens out as your all-in threat starts to force respect on her.","Level 6 Purgatory lets you totem-execute her below threshold after a slow-in.","Post-items it's a skill coinflip — her Valor disengage offsets your burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"renekton","win":["Renekton","Renekton","Renekton","Renekton","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With Fury-empowered Cull the Meek (Q) healing and the Slice-and-Dice (E) stun combo, Renekton hard-wins any short trade; his point-and-click stun on empowered W also cancels your E reset dash, so never contest him while he has bars."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"At 6 Purgatory (R) is your equalizer: after he dumps his E-Q-W combo and burns Fury he has no dash to escape, so drop the totem and execute him below the rising threshold before he can Slice back to safety."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your first AP item plus W grey-health lets you punish his cooldown windows — if he blows Slice-and-Dice to engage, blink E through him and totem when he's low, since he can't disengage without both E charges."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late his Dominus (R) tankiness and empowered stun make extended fights ugly for a squishy assassin; you want the game decided on picks where you catch him with dashes down rather than a straight bruiser duel."}],"wants":{"you":["Renekton's Fury bar empty and both Slice-and-Dice charges spent","level 6 so Purgatory punishes his post-combo low-HP window","W grey-health up before you blink E in to burst"],"foe":["Fury-empowered W stun to cancel your E dash and lock you down","short all-in trades where his Q lifesteal out-sustains you","early lead to snowball his mid-game tankiness with Dominus"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 Renekton bullies you: his Cull the Meek (Q) is a wide sustain-heavy swing that out-trades your auto pressure, and he generates Fury fast to empower it. Your Silver Stake wants extended windows he simply doesn't give — take short CS and stay out of Q range until he steps too deep.","mid":"Levels 3-5 he owns the lane with the Slice-and-Dice (E) dash into empowered Ruthless Predator (W) stun. That point-and-click stun interrupts your E reset dash mid-animation, so any all-in he initiates on cooldown he wins. Farm safely, track his Fury, and wait — this window is his and pushing it loses games.","late":"At 6 the matchup flips your way for one clean window: Purgatory executes him after he commits his combo and has no Slice left to escape. Beyond first item it settles into a skill fight — your W-and-E burst deletes him when his dashes are down, but his Dominus tankiness and stun make a fair extended duel a loss, so pick your engages around his cooldowns.","whys":["Renekton's level-1 Q swing out-sustains and out-trades your auto pressure.","At 2 his Fury generation empowers Q healing, keeping him ahead in short trades.","Level 3 Slice-and-Dice plus empowered W stun wins every all-in he starts.","Levels 4-5 his dash-stun cancels your E reset, so he controls the tempo.","At 5 it evens as your ult threat looms and forces him to respect your all-in.","Level 6 Purgatory executes him post-combo when his Slice charges are spent.","Post-items it's a skill fight — your burst answers his tankiness on even footing."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"riven","win":["Riven","Riven","Riven","Riven","Riven","Riven","Riven"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Riven's three Broken Wings (Q) dashes plus Valor (E) shield and Ki Burst (W) stun give her a full mobile combo that out-trades and out-maneuvers you at every point; her E shield eats your W burst and her stun cancels your E dash."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even at 6 Purgatory struggles: her Blade of the Exile (R) gives her range and a second-charge burst, and her Q mobility lets her dash out of your totem radius before the execute lands."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With her first item Riven's shield-heavy burst chunks you before you can set up E-reset; you need her to whiff Ki Burst stun to get any all-in, and her Valor mobility usually resets the spacing."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Riven remains a mobility nightmare for a squishy assassin — her Q dashes and R re-cast let her both engage and disengage your commits, so this stays a losing skill-and-mechanics check throughout."}],"wants":{"you":["Riven's Ki Burst (W) stun on cooldown or whiffed","all three Broken Wings charges dumped so she can't dash out of your totem","W grey-health and E reset both up before you force a trade"],"foe":["Q dash stacks plus E shield to win and escape every trade","Ki Burst stun to cancel your E gap-close mid-dash","kill pressure to snowball her item-spike burst"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 Riven starts winning immediately: Broken Wings (Q) lets her dash in, auto-cancel, and dash out faster than your Silver Stake pressure can punish, and she takes W first for an early stun. You have no way to pin her down, so give ground, farm carefully, and never walk into Q range at low levels.","mid":"Levels 3-6 are her strongest window. Her full kit — three Q dashes, Valor (E) shield, and Ki Burst (W) stun — lets her out-trade you and cancel your E reset with the stun. Your totem at 6 barely helps because her Q mobility and Blade of the Exile (R) let her dash clear of the execute radius. This whole stretch is hers; play for farm and jungle help.","late":"Post-items Riven stays ahead. Her shield absorbs your W-burst opener and her mobility means every commit you make can be dashed out of, while her R gives both extra damage and a repositioning tool. This is a mechanics matchup where her mobility hard-counters your need to stick to a target — win it with ganks and roams, not solo duels.","whys":["Riven's level-1 Q auto-cancels let her out-trade and escape your pressure.","At 2 her early Ki Burst stun and dash mobility keep her firmly ahead.","Level 3 her full Q-E-W combo out-trades you and cancels your E dash.","Levels 4-5 her shield eats your burst and her dashes deny any all-in.","Level 6 her R and Q mobility let her dash out of Purgatory's radius.","At first item her shield-heavy burst out-damages your setup window.","Late her Q and R mobility hard-counter your need to stick a squishy target."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"rumble","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Rumble's Flamespitter (Q) shreds you in melee range but has a short window before overheat; bait the Q, walk out, and re-engage on the cooldown when his heat is spent and he can't Electro-Harpoon (E) slow-chain you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"At 6 Purgatory is a clean win: The Equalizer (R) is a channel with a telegraph, and once he's committed his flamethrower you can Q-slow, E-dash in, and totem-execute him below threshold before his shield and heat can save him."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first AP item your W grey-health steroid plus E reset bursts him faster than his Danger Zone shielding can absorb; punish any moment his heat bar is high and Q is winding down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Rumble is a teamfight ult-bot, but 1v1 in a side lane your assassin burst and E mobility beat his short-range zoning, so you keep the lane edge as long as you dodge his ult carpet."}],"wants":{"you":["Rumble's heat bar high or overheated so his Q and E go on lockout","level 6 to execute him out of his telegraphed R channel","W and E up to burst through his Danger Zone shield"],"foe":["Flamespitter (Q) uptime with fresh heat to shred you in melee","Electro-Harpoon (E) slows to kite your E gap-close","landing The Equalizer (R) carpet to zone your all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 it's an even skill lane: Rumble's Flamespitter (Q) does big DPS if you stand in it, but it burns heat fast and leaves him exposed on the cooldown. Trade around his heat bar — step in when he's overheated, back off when it's fresh — and your Silver Stake on-hit keeps pace since he has no hard lock on you.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay a coinflip decided by heat management and E usage. His Electro-Harpoon (E) double-slow can peel your E dash, but if you save your gap-close for after he throws a harpoon you close freely. Respect Danger Zone empowered Q, but punish every overheat — this window rewards whoever tracks the heat bar better.","late":"At 6 you gain the edge: Purgatory executes him cleanly out of his telegraphed Equalizer channel, and your first-item W-and-E burst outpaces his shield. Late-game he's a teamfight ultimate carry, but in a solo side-lane your mobility and burst keep you ahead of his short-range zoning as long as you sidestep the ult carpet.","whys":["Level 1 is even — his Q DPS is offset by heat cost and your on-hit pressure.","At 2 trades stay skill-based around his heat bar and your dodging.","Level 3 his E slows can peel you, but overheat windows keep it even.","Levels 4-5 stay a coinflip decided by heat management on both sides.","At 5 it's still even as his empowered Q trades against your all-in threat.","Level 6 Purgatory executes him out of his telegraphed R channel for the win.","Post-items it evens again — his shield answers your burst in a fair fight."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"ryze","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Ryze"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ryze's Overload (Q) reset off Rune Prison (W) root gives him rapid poke, but his root has a tell; if he lands W on you he chains a full Q rotation, so dodge the point-blank W and his damage falls off a cliff."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"At 6 it stays even — Realm Warp (R) is a macro tool, not a duel button, so 1v1 you can still Q-slow into E and threaten a totem execute if he burns W to root and it whiffs."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Ryze's first mana item is a huge power spike: his Q spam becomes a wall of damage and his shield-and-flux burst starts to out-DPS your assassin window, so all-in only when W is down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Ryze out-scales you hard — mana-stacked Q-E flux detonations and his passive shield make him a raid boss who can root and kite you before you close, so the lane tilts to him with items."}],"wants":{"you":["Ryze's Rune Prison (W) root dodged or on cooldown","W grey-health and E reset up to blink in during his Q downtime","to end the lane before his mana items come online"],"foe":["landing W root to chain a full Overload (Q) reset combo","first mana item to spike his Q spam and shield uptime","scaling into late-game where his flux burst out-DPSes you"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 it's an even skill lane: Ryze pokes with Overload (Q) but you can walk up on the cooldown and pressure with Silver Stake on-hit. His damage is entirely gated by whether Rune Prison (W) lands to enable his Q reset, so respect the root range and trade in the gaps.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay even and revolve around his W. If you dodge Rune Prison his combo fizzles and you can Q-slow, E-blink in, and threaten burst; if you eat the root he chains Q-E-flux for heavy damage. Play around that one button — your mobility lets you bait it. His level-6 R is a map tool, so it doesn't shift the duel.","late":"After his first mana item the matchup tips to Ryze and only worsens. Stacked mana turns his Q into relentless AoE damage, his passive shield blunts your all-in, and his root plus kite keeps you off him before your W-and-E burst can land. This is a scaling loss — press your even early-mid windows hard and get help before his items come online.","whys":["Level 1 is even — his Q poke is answered by your on-hit walk-ups.","At 2 trades stay skill-based and gated by his W root landing.","Level 3 dodging Rune Prison keeps his Q combo in check for an even lane.","Levels 4-5 stay even, revolving around who wins the root mind-game.","At 5 it's still even before his mana items come online.","Level 6 stays even since Realm Warp is macro, not a dueling tool.","Post-items Ryze's mana-stacked Q spam and shield out-scale and out-DPS you."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"sejuani","win":["Sejuani","Sejuani","Sejuani","Sejuani","Skill","Skill","Sejuani"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Sejuani's Frost Armor passive plus Arctic Assault (Q) charge gives her a tanky engage that shrugs off your burst; her Permafrost (E) stun off Frost stacks locks you down and cancels your E dash, so never fight into a stacked target."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"At 6 Glacial Prison (R) is a long-range flash-stun that hard-CCs you before you can set up Purgatory; her tankiness also means she rarely drops low enough for the totem to execute in a straight fight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With armor and HP items Sejuani becomes nearly unkillable in a duel — your W-and-E burst barely dents her while her Permafrost stun and slows keep you pinned, so you cannot solo her."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Sejuani is a full tank engage bot; you'll never execute her one-on-one, so your job is to dodge her R in fights and delete her backline instead of trading with her."}],"wants":{"you":["Sejuani's Frost stacks reset so Permafrost (E) can't stun you","to avoid her entirely and farm side waves rather than duel","roams and picks on her squishies instead of a hopeless 1v1"],"foe":["Frost stacks on you to land the Permafrost (E) stun","Arctic Assault (Q) engage into your dash to cancel your E","landing Glacial Prison (R) to lock you before you can totem"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 Sejuani already wins: Frost Armor makes her a wall your Silver Stake on-hit can't crack, and Arctic Assault (Q) lets her charge in and apply Frost stacks toward a stun. You do zero meaningful damage to her health bar, so just farm at range and treat every step forward as stun-bait.","mid":"Levels 3-6 she owns the lane. Once she has Permafrost (E) up, any Frost-stacked target eats a point-and-click stun that cancels your E reset dash mid-animation, and her passive shielding means your all-in fizzles. At 6 Glacial Prison adds a long-range lockdown. There's no trade window here — farm, ping for jungle pressure, and don't feed her engage.","late":"Post-items the matchup is a hard loss in a duel: stacked armor and health make her effectively un-executable by Purgatory, while her stun-and-slow kit keeps you glued in place. Stop trying to kill her — sidestep her Glacial Prison in teamfights, use your E mobility to reach her carries, and let her be a stat-check you simply avoid one-on-one.","whys":["Sejuani's level-1 Frost Armor shrugs off your on-hit pressure entirely.","At 2 Arctic Assault engage and Frost stacks keep her firmly ahead.","Level 3 Permafrost stun cancels your E dash and locks down any trade.","Levels 4-5 her passive shielding and stun deny every all-in you attempt.","At 5 it briefly evens as your ult threat forces a little respect.","Level 6 stays even-ish before her tank items and R lockdown take over.","Late her stacked armor and HP make her un-executable and un-duelable."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"sett","win":["Sett","Sett","Sett","Sett","Skill","Skill","Sett"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Sett's Haymaker (W) stores your damage into a grey-health true-damage punch, so the harder you burst him the harder he hits back; his Knuckle Down (Q) slow plus Grit shield make him win every extended trade at this stage."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"At 6 The Show Stopper (R) suppresses and displaces you before you can line up Purgatory; his Grit shield keeps him topped up, so he rarely drops into your totem's execute threshold in a fair fight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With his first bruiser item Sett's Haymaker punch and W shield make him a brick — your W-and-E burst feeds his stored grey health, and his R suppress can cancel your all-in on reaction."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Sett is a durable duelist who punishes committed burst; you want to poke and disengage or pick him with dashes down rather than trade into his stored-damage W."}],"wants":{"you":["Sett's Haymaker (W) on cooldown so your burst isn't stored and returned","to avoid feeding grey health — poke and reset, don't full-commit","the Show Stopper (R) baited out before you all-in"],"foe":["storing your burst into Haymaker (W) for a true-damage counter-punch","landing Knuckle Down (Q) slow and Facebreaker (E) to pin you","hitting The Show Stopper (R) to suppress and cancel your dash"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 Sett wins the lane: Grit passive gives him a free shield every fight and his auto attacks hit hard, so your Silver Stake on-hit trades come back on you worse. Worse, dumping damage into him charges Haymaker (W). Farm at range, don't feed his W, and only step up when his Grit shield is spent.","mid":"Levels 3-6 he controls the trades. Knuckle Down (Q) slows you into his Facebreaker (E) pull, and his stored Haymaker punches for true damage scaled off the burst you just did — so your all-in literally arms his counter. His shield keeps him healthy, so he rarely drops to a threatenable level. Play safe and look for jungle help rather than solo trades.","late":"Post-items Sett is a wall that punishes commitment. Your W-and-E burst pours into his grey-health W and comes back as a true-damage haymaker, while The Show Stopper (R) suppresses you and cancels your E dash on reaction. Don't full-commit into him — poke, disengage, and only engage when his W and R are down or catch him repositioning in fights.","whys":["Sett's level-1 Grit shield and heavy autos turn your trades against you.","At 2 his auto pressure and shield keep him ahead in every exchange.","Level 3 Knuckle Down slow into Facebreaker pins you for his combo.","Levels 4-5 his stored Haymaker punishes your burst with a true-damage return.","At 5 it briefly evens as your ult threat forces some respect.","Level 6 stays even-ish before his R suppress and tankiness take over.","Late his Haymaker return and R suppress make committing into him a loss."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"shen","win":["Shen","Shen","Shen","Shen","Skill","Skill","Shen"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Shen's spike, not yours: with Q (Twilight Assault) up he shreds your grey-health from W (Soul Ignition) with the empowered on-hits and out-trades you at melee range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Neither of you truly flips lane at 6 — your R (Purgatory) can execute him if you catch him low, but his R (Stand United) means he's rarely alone and can shield-dash a dying ally, so this phase is a wash."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still even after your first item; your burst comes online but his Spirit's Refuge (W) blocks your AA-reliant Silver Stake (P) procs during a trade."},{"when":"Late","text":"Shen scales into a tanky global-pressure monster — his roams with R decide the map while your single-target execute struggles to matter through his sustain and shields."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke him below the R (Purgatory) threshold before he can W to negate your on-hits","Use E (Ashen Pursuit) to dodge his Q vorpal-sword taunt-window","Roam or reset when he TPs bot so his global doesn't out-tempo you"],"foe":["Land Q (Twilight Assault) so the empowered orbs shred your grey-health","Time W (Spirit's Refuge) to eat your Silver Stake AA procs during your all-in","Use R (Stand United) to swing a fight elsewhere and snowball a lane he's not in"]},"early":"Shen wins the early exchanges here — respect his level-2/3 Q (Twilight Assault) which slows and hits hard, and never W into him while his Spirit's Refuge is up because it eats every Silver Stake on-hit you rely on. Farm safe, take short trades only when his Q is on cooldown.","mid":"Through 6 the lane stays Shen-favoured: he sustains your poke, shields his own trades, and his R (Stand United) lets him leave lane even if you shove. Your only real windows are Q-mark burst combos when his W is down, and using E's reset to punish an over-extended taunt.","late":"Post-items Shen out-scales you as a tank with a global ult — your single-target R (Purgatory) execute is easy to shield or peel around, and he dictates the map with roams. Prioritise objectives and side-lane pressure while your team answers his R.","whys":["Shen-favoured: his level-1 Q on-hits and durability beat your early poke.","Shen-favoured: at 2 his Q slow lets him force trades you lose in melee.","Shen-favoured: level-3 Spirit's Refuge (W) negates your Silver Stake procs in every all-in.","Shen-favoured: through 4-5 his sustain and shields grind down your grey-health steroid.","Skill: at 6 your R execute answers his R's map pressure — the fight is even.","Skill: first-item burst arrives for you but his W-block keeps the trade a coin-flip.","Shen-favoured: with items he scales into a tanky global roamer your execute can't punish."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"singed","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Skill phase: Singed wants to proxy and fling you into his minions, but if you land Q (Ritual Nails) marks and stack Silver Stake on-hits you can chunk him whenever he Fling (E) whiffs or he walks up to poison-tick you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your spike: R (Purgatory) turns his low-HP escapes into a death sentence — a Singed who trades poison ticks and drops below the growing threshold gets executed even mid-flee."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After your first item your burst comfortably outpaces his poison DPS in a straight fight; just don't chase him through his W (Mega Adhesive) slow zone."},{"when":"Late","text":"Singed becomes a slippery tank who runs it down and flings your carries — the lane matters less than whether your team can peel his engage."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait his Fling (E) with E (Ashen Pursuit), then blink in for Q marks and free on-hits","Hold R (Purgatory) for the moment his poison self-ticks him low on the retreat","Avoid his W (Mega Adhesive) + Fling combo that sets up ganks"],"foe":["Proxy the wave and drag you into his minions/jungler","Fling (E) you into his turret or a Mega Adhesive slow field","Stack HP and run it down, using poison to whittle you while kiting"]},"early":"This is a skill lane early — Singed will proxy and try to Fling (E) you into a bad spot, so respect his positioning and don't chase into fog. When he walks up to poison-tick the wave, punish with Q (Ritual Nails) marks and Silver Stake on-hits; you win any exchange where his Fling is on cooldown.","mid":"Through 4-5 it stays even and comes down to whether you dodge his Fling and W (Mega Adhesive) setups. Use E (Ashen Pursuit) to bait the Fling, then commit — your grey-health steroid from W (Soul Ignition) lets you out-trade his poison in a short window.","late":"At 6 you spike hard: R (Purgatory) executes a Singed who has poison-ticked himself low while running, flipping his signature escape into your kill. Beyond first item your burst wins the 1v1, but late-game he shifts to a run-it-down flinger, so late the lane is a wash decided by team peel.","whys":["Skill: level 1 is even — his poison trades against your on-hit poke.","Skill: at 2 the lane hinges on dodging his Fling, not raw stats.","Skill: level 3 stays even; his Mega Adhesive setups balance your Q burst.","Skill: through 4-5 it's still a coin-flip around his Fling cooldown.","Skill: at 6 his HP and mobility offset your fresh ult in a straight fight.","Locke-favoured: your R (Purgatory) executes his low-HP poison retreats.","Skill: with items his tanky run-it-down style neutralises your single-target burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"sion","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Sion","Skill","Sion","Sion"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Sion's spike arrives at 4: with a point in Q (Decimating Smash) charged and E (Roar of the Slayer) to poke, his knockup threat lets him zone you off the wave and win extended trades."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Sion-favoured: his R (Unstoppable Onslaught) is a lane-changing engage and, with his passive zombie form, killing him just spawns a raging attacker — your R (Purgatory) execute is blunted because he keeps fighting after 'dying'."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Sion's HP/resist stacking outpaces your burst; his charged Q knockup into E can chunk you before your Silver Stake on-hits do enough."},{"when":"Late","text":"Sion is a tanky engage cannon whose zombie passive laughs at your single-target execute — the fight is decided by his R flank, not the 1v1."}],"wants":{"you":["Sidestep his Q (Decimating Smash) charge with E (Ashen Pursuit) to deny the knockup","Trade only when his Q and E are down, stacking Q marks fast","Track his R (Unstoppable Onslaught) and dodge the engage rather than duel it"],"foe":["Land a fully-charged Q knockup to lock you for a full combo","Poke with E (Roar of the Slayer) to keep his passive shield and HP advantage","Use R to engage or split your team, then brawl on in zombie form"]},"early":"Early is a skill phase — respect his charged Q (Decimating Smash), which knocks you up for a full trade, and his E (Roar of the Slayer) poke. Farm carefully and only step up for Q (Ritual Nails) marks when his abilities are down; your on-hits do work but his shield passive eats a lot of it.","mid":"From level 4 Sion tilts the lane his way: his knockup threat zones you, and at 6 his R (Unstoppable Onslaught) plus zombie passive make him nearly un-killable in lane — even a good R (Purgatory) execute just sends him into raging zombie form to keep swinging. Don't over-commit into his engage.","late":"With items Sion out-scales you hard as a tanky initiator; his passive undoing of 'kills' neutralises your execute totem and his R dictates fights. Play for side-lane tempo and let your team handle his engage rather than trying to solo him.","whys":["Skill: level 1 is even — his shield passive trades against your on-hits.","Skill: at 2 neither snowballs; it hinges on his Q charge timing.","Skill: level 3 stays even before his knockup spike lands.","Sion-favoured: at 4 his charged Q + E poke let him zone you off farm.","Skill: at 6 the lane briefly evens as your R answers his engage threat.","Sion-favoured: his zombie passive undoes your execute, so 6 tilts back to him.","Sion-favoured: with items his HP-stacking and R engage overwhelm your single-target burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"swain","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Skill phase: Swain wants to land W (Vision of Empire) and E (Nevermove) to root you for his Q barrage, but if you dodge the slow-moving E with E (Ashen Pursuit) you can punish his long cooldowns with Q marks and on-hits."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your spike: Swain's R (Demonic Ascension) heals him as he fights, but R (Purgatory) executes him below the totem threshold before his soul-drain can top him back up — the execute beats his sustain."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After first item your burst outraces his ramp; kill him before his R heal-tick stabilises the fight and he can't scale into you."},{"when":"Late","text":"If Swain survives to full items he's a durable teamfight drain-tank — the lane matters less than whether you converted your 6 spike into a lead."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge his E (Nevermove) root with E (Ashen Pursuit) so his Q combo whiffs","All-in on his root/W cooldowns when he can't peel","Use R (Purgatory) to execute through his R (Demonic Ascension) heal"],"foe":["Land E (Nevermove) into a full Q (Death's Hand) barrage while W-marked","Ramp Grand Hegemony stacks so his R sustain outlasts your burst","Sit back and farm safely, scaling into an unkillable drain-tank"]},"early":"Skill lane early — Swain's main threat is E (Nevermove), a delayed root that sets up his Q (Death's Hand) barrage, so bait or dodge it with your E (Ashen Pursuit) blink. When his root and W are down he's exposed; step in for Q (Ritual Nails) marks and Silver Stake on-hits.","mid":"Through 4-5 it stays even and revolves around his E cooldown — eat a root and you take a big Q combo, dodge it and you win the trade. Use W (Soul Ignition) grey-health to survive his poke while you close the gap on his long-cooldown windows.","late":"At 6 you spike: R (Purgatory) executes Swain even through his R (Demonic Ascension) drain heal, so a clean all-in on his rooted-and-low state kills him before he stabilises. After first item your burst still wins, but if he reaches full items he becomes a durable drain-tank, so late the lane evens out.","whys":["Skill: level 1 is even — his Q poke against your on-hit trades.","Skill: at 2 the lane hinges on whether his E lands, not raw stats.","Skill: level 3 stays even around his root cooldown.","Skill: through 4-5 dodging E keeps the trades a coin-flip.","Skill: at 6 his R heal offsets your fresh ult in a drawn-out fight.","Locke-favoured: R (Purgatory) executes him through his R drain before it stabilises.","Skill: with items his drain-tank scaling neutralises your single-target burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"sylas","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Skill phase: Sylas wants to E-in (Abscond/Abduct), Q (Chain Lash) the double-detonation, and W (Kingslayer) to heal off the trade — dodge his Q with E (Ashen Pursuit) and his sustain evaporates, letting your on-hits win."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your spike: your R (Purgatory) executes him below the threshold before his W (Kingslayer) low-HP heal can save him, and you don't hand him a stolen ult worth flipping the lane."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After first item your burst outpaces his — race him down before his W heal-tick and grey-health from your W (Soul Ignition) let you win the flat DPS trade."},{"when":"Late","text":"Sylas scales into a slippery skirmisher who steals a game-changing ult in fights — the 1v1 lane matters less than his roam and ult-theft value."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge his Q (Chain Lash) second detonation with E (Ashen Pursuit)","Bait his E (Abduct) then blink in for Q marks and Silver Stake on-hits","Use R (Purgatory) to execute through his W (Kingslayer) heal"],"foe":["Land the Q double-hit and W (Kingslayer) to heal the trade back","Use E (Abscond/Abduct) to poke then disengage on cooldown","Scale and roam, stealing a high-impact ult in the next fight"]},"early":"Skill lane early — Sylas pokes with Q (Chain Lash) and heals trades with W (Kingslayer), so the key is dodging his Q's second detonation using E (Ashen Pursuit). When his Q and E (Abduct) are down he has no sustain engine; step up for Q (Ritual Nails) marks and free on-hits.","mid":"Through 4-5 it's an even skirmish decided by whether you eat his Q combo — his W heal makes drawn-out trades favour him, so keep exchanges short and lean on your W (Soul Ignition) grey-health to survive his burst. Punish every whiffed Abduct.","late":"At 6 you spike: R (Purgatory) executes a low Sylas before his W (Kingslayer) heal saves him, and you avoid feeding a strong ult-steal. After first item your burst wins the race, but if he scales he becomes a slippery ult-thief in teamfights, so late the lane evens out.","whys":["Skill: level 1 is even — his Q poke against your on-hit trades.","Skill: at 2 the lane hinges on dodging his Q, not raw stats.","Skill: level 3 stays even around his W-healed trades.","Skill: through 4-5 short trades keep the matchup a coin-flip.","Skill: at 6 his W heal and mobility offset your fresh ult in a long fight.","Locke-favoured: R (Purgatory) executes him through his Kingslayer heal.","Skill: with items his ult-theft and mobility neutralise your single-target burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"tahmkench","win":["Tahm Kench","Tahm Kench","Tahm Kench","Tahm Kench","Skill","Skill","Tahm Kench"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Tahm's phase: his passive (An Acquired Taste) stacks off Q (Tongue Lash) and AAs, and a full three-stack proc plus his W (Abyssal Dive) makes his trades brutal while his grey-health passive shrugs off your poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Roughly even at 6 — your R (Purgatory) can execute him if he's low, but his W (Devour) self-cast and passive grey-health heal make it hard to burst him below threshold in one go."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even-ish, but tilting back to him: his HP stacking blunts your first-item burst and his Q slow into passive stacks still out-trades you up close."},{"when":"Late","text":"Tahm becomes an unkillable peel-tank who eats your carries with W (Devour) — your single-target execute barely dents his stacked HP and shielding."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge his Q (Tongue Lash) so he can't build passive stacks or slow you","Fight only when his passive stacks and W are down","Save R (Purgatory) for a clean low-HP window before his grey-health heals him"],"foe":["Land Q (Tongue Lash) to slow and stack An Acquired Taste for the stun proc","Use W (Abyssal Dive) to close and trade under his grey-health passive","Stack HP and scale into a peel-tank that devours your carries"]},"early":"Tahm Kench wins the early lane — his passive An Acquired Taste stacks off Q (Tongue Lash) and autos toward a mini-stun, and his grey-health regen shrugs off your poke. Respect his Q slow, don't get greedy into a three-stack proc, and farm patiently rather than forcing trades you'll lose.","mid":"Through 4-5 it stays Tahm-favoured: his W (Abyssal Dive) engage plus passive stacks and HP make him the stronger duelist, and your W (Soul Ignition) grey-health gets out-sustained. Only step up when his passive stacks are fresh-reset and his Q is down.","late":"At 6 the lane briefly evens as your R (Purgatory) threatens an execute, but his passive grey-health heal makes it tough to keep him below threshold. Post-items he out-scales you into an unkillable peel-tank who eats your carries with W (Devour); play for tempo elsewhere and don't invest into a losing 1v1.","whys":["Tahm-favoured: his level-1 passive stacks and grey-health beat your poke.","Tahm-favoured: at 2 his Q slow sets up trades you lose in melee.","Tahm-favoured: level-3 W engage plus passive stacks out-trade you.","Tahm-favoured: through 4-5 his HP and sustain grind down your steroid.","Skill: at 6 your R execute threat evens the lane briefly.","Skill: first-item burst arrives but his grey-health heal keeps 6 a coin-flip.","Tahm-favoured: with items he scales into a peel-tank your execute can't punish."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"teemo","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Skill phase: Teemo's Q (Blinding Dart) shuts off your AA-reliant Silver Stake (P) on-hits, so time your all-in for when his Q is on cooldown and his E (Toxic Shot) poison isn't stacked high."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your spike: Teemo is squishy, so R (Purgatory) reliably executes him below threshold — one committed E (Ashen Pursuit) blink into your combo and he can't survive under the totem."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After first item your burst deletes him if you reach him; the whole fight is just getting past his Q blind and shroom (R) zones."},{"when":"Late","text":"Teemo's shroom (R) map control and DPS matter more than the lane — if you snowballed 6 you're fine, otherwise his poke and mushrooms zone your team."}],"wants":{"you":["All-in when his Q (Blinding Dart) is down so your on-hits land","Use E (Ashen Pursuit) to close the gap before his poison/blind stacks up","Execute the squishy Teemo with R (Purgatory) the moment he's low"],"foe":["Blind you with Q (Blinding Dart) to cancel your Silver Stake on-hits","Kite with movespeed passive and stack E (Toxic Shot) poison","Zone you with shroom (R) fields and out-range your approach"]},"early":"Skill lane early — Teemo's Q (Blinding Dart) is the whole matchup, since a well-timed blind cancels your AA-based Silver Stake (P) on-hits mid-trade. Farm through his E (Toxic Shot) poke and only step up when his Q is on cooldown; his squishiness means any clean trade goes your way.","mid":"Through 4-5 it stays even and hinges on his Q timing — eat the blind and you lose the trade, catch it down and you win hard. Use E (Ashen Pursuit) to close before his poison and movespeed let him kite, and lean on W (Soul Ignition) grey-health to survive the approach.","late":"At 6 you spike: Teemo is squishy, so R (Purgatory) executes him reliably once you land a committed all-in past the blind. Post-items your burst deletes him on contact, but if he survives he pivots to shroom (R) map control, so late the lane comes down to whether you converted your 6 kill pressure.","whys":["Skill: level 1 is even — his poison poke against your on-hit trades.","Skill: at 2 the lane hinges on his Q blind timing, not raw stats.","Skill: level 3 stays even around his Blinding Dart cooldown.","Skill: through 4-5 the trades are a coin-flip decided by his blind.","Skill: at 6 his kite and blind offset your fresh ult before you close.","Locke-favoured: R (Purgatory) reliably executes the squishy Teemo once you reach him.","Skill: with items his shroom map control offsets your on-contact burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"trundle","win":["Trundle","Trundle","Trundle","Trundle","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Trundle owns these levels: his Chomp (Q) bite steals AD and heals, and Frozen Domain (E) turns any fight into his zone with attack-speed and sustain, so trading nails (Q) into him just feeds his bite windows."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Purgatory (R) is the reset button here: Subjugate (R) steals your HP and resistances, but if you save your execute totem for after his ult you can still drop him under the threshold and delete him before he outsustains it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Once you complete your first AP item the burst on Q marks plus W grey-health steroid catches up, and a single all-in with E blink resets on the takedown lets you snowball off his low base durability."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late is dictated by Skill and totem placement: don't ult him at full sustain, but a coordinated collapse where you Purgatory him mid-Subjugate flips the fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Save Purgatory (R) until after his Subjugate (R) is committed","Trade in short bursts, then E out before his Frozen Domain (E) heals him back","Buy an anti-heal item early to blunt Chomp (Q) lifesteal"],"foe":["Sit inside Frozen Domain (E) so every trade heals and speeds him","Bite you with Chomp (Q) whenever your W self-damage has chunked you","Use Pillar (W) to wall off your E escape and force extended trades"]},"early":"Trundle bullies levels 1-3: his Chomp bite steals your AD while healing him, so avoid greedy Q-nail trades that let him bite back into free sustain. Respect that his Frozen Domain arriving at 3 turns any skirmish into his home turf, and your W self-damage only helps his bite math. Farm safe, poke with Q from max range, and don't commit E until you have a burst window.","mid":"Through 4-6 Trundle stays ahead on stats and sustain, but level 6 is your inflection point. Purgatory is the great equalizer: don't waste it into his Subjugate, hold it until he's committed and drop him under the growing execute threshold. Pop W for the grey-health steroid only when you can convert the trade, and use E's takedown reset to escape or chase.","late":"With one AP item and anti-heal your burst outruns his sustain in a clean burst, though extended fights inside his Domain still favor him. Skill decides teamfights: land Q marks, W for the damage spike, and time Purgatory on him after he blows Subjugate so the execute lands before his healing catches up.","whys":["Trundle's Chomp bite steals AD and heals, bullying level 1.","His sustain and bite math beat your self-damaging trades at 2.","Frozen Domain at 3 turns every skirmish into his healing zone.","He stays ahead on stolen stats and sustain through 4-5.","Even at 6 your Purgatory neutralizes his Subjugate if timed right.","Your first-item burst plus a saved execute totem lets you delete him.","Late fights come down to Skill and whether you ult him post-Subjugate."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"tryndamere","win":["Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere","Tryndamere"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Tryndamere is winning already: his Spinning Slash (E) gap-closes onto you and his crit-fueled autos plus Bloodlust (Q) heal shred you faster than your Q nails and W burst can answer, and your W self-damage only speeds his Fury build."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Undying Rage (R) is the wall your entire kit crashes into: Purgatory (R) is an execute totem, but he cannot die under 5 seconds of guaranteed survival, so your ult is dead value the moment he flips it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Even after your first AP item he simply presses R to survive your combo, heals to full with Bloodlust (Q), and E's onto you the next window; his crit scaling outpaces your single burst."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late he is a permanent threat: your Purgatory can never execute through Undying Rage, and his mobility plus crit makes him a backline-diving nightmare you can only kite, never delete."}],"wants":{"you":["Play for CS and roams instead of solo kills you cannot secure","Bank Purgatory (R) only for after his Undying Rage (R) expires","Rush anti-heal to cut his Bloodlust (Q) sustain in half"],"foe":["Stack Fury off your W self-damage trades, then all-in with Spinning Slash (E)","Flip Undying Rage (R) the instant your execute totem drops","Chase resets with E through minions since it refreshes on kills"]},"early":"This is a losing lane from level 1. Tryndamere's autos and Bloodlust heal outpace your Q-nail poke, and every time your W self-damage chunks you he converts it into Fury for a bigger spin crit. Do not try to win short trades; farm at max range, use E purely defensively to disengage his Spinning Slash, and give up the lane rather than the kill.","mid":"Levels 4-6 he only gets scarier as Fury crits ramp. The core problem is level 6: Undying Rage makes him unkillable for its duration, which is a hard counter to your execute-totem identity. Never blow Purgatory while his R is up or available. Farm, ping for jungle pressure, and treat every all-in he starts as something you survive rather than win.","late":"With items he is a full-blown carry threat and your ult remains blanked by Undying Rage. Anti-heal and a frontline are your only tools; Purgatory can only ever land in the sliver after his R expires. Accept the lane loss, scale, and rely on your team to lock him during the Undying Rage window so you can clean up after.","whys":["His autos and Bloodlust heal outtrade your level-1 nails.","Fury crits and E gap-close overwhelm you at level 2.","Spinning Slash plus sustain owns the level-3 all-in.","His crit scaling keeps him ahead through levels 4-5.","Undying Rage hard-counters your execute totem at 6.","Post-item he still survives your burst with R and heals back.","Late, Purgatory can never execute through his guaranteed survival."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"urgot","win":["Urgot","Urgot","Urgot","Urgot","Urgot","Urgot","Urgot"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Urgot dominates: Corrosive Charge (Q) zones your CS, Purge (W) shreds you the moment you step into range, and your W self-damage plus melee-range Q nails walk you straight into his sustained damage."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Fear Beyond Death (R) is your worst nightmare as an execute champ: he also executes below a threshold, but his flip is a hard suppress that yanks you back, so racing him to the kill line usually means you die to his R first."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After first item his tankiness and Purge shred outstat your single burst; you chunk him, he presses W and W-Q's you back to even while his passive shields keep him healthy."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Urgot is a durable executioner who beats you at your own game: his R suppress-executes through your escape, and your E blink can't outrun a well-aimed Disdain (E) knockback into his kill zone."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge Corrosive Charge (Q) so you aren't stuck in his Purge (W) range","Never race his Fear Beyond Death (R) execute with your own low HP","Buy anti-heal and armor to survive his sustained Purge shred"],"foe":["Zone your wave with Corrosive Charge (Q) then chunk you with Purge (W)","Land Disdain (E) to flip you into minions and free damage","Flip you with Fear Beyond Death (R) to suppress-execute before your Purgatory lands"]},"early":"Urgot wins the lane from the first recall onward. His Corrosive Charge slows and zones you off CS, and the instant you enter your melee Q-nail or W range his Purge shreds you down. Your W self-damage makes this worse, handing him free execute math. Farm from distance, respect the Q slow window, and hold E to disengage rather than to engage.","mid":"Through 4-6 he only tightens the vice, and level 6 is genuinely dangerous. Fear Beyond Death is a hard suppress-execute that answers your Purgatory directly: if you both dip low, his flip yanks and locks you for the kill before your totem can finish him. Do not play the execute race. Give up plates if needed and look to reset rather than trade into his Purge.","late":"Late Urgot is a tanky executioner who beats your identity outright. His R suppresses through your E blink and his Disdain knockback can flip you into his kill zone. Anti-heal and armor help you survive, but you cannot solo him; play around teammates who can body-block Disdain and burn his R, then clean up only when his execute is on cooldown.","whys":["Corrosive Charge and Purge shred out-trade your level-1 poke.","His W shred and zone control own level 2 in his range.","Purge plus Q slow dominate the level-3 all-in.","His tankiness and sustained damage keep him ahead through 4-5.","Fear Beyond Death hard-counters your execute race at 6.","Post-item his shred and durability outstat your single burst.","Late, his suppress-execute beats your Purgatory and E escape."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"vayne","win":["Vayne","Vayne","Vayne","Vayne","Vayne","Vayne","Vayne"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Vayne kites you cleanly: Tumble (Q) repositions out of your Q-nail range, Silver Bolts (W) true-damage every third hit chunks you through your grey health, and Condemn (E) stuns you against a wall the moment you E in."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Final Hour (R) gives her stealth on Tumble and a huge AD steroid, so even your Purgatory setup gets kited; she invisibly repositions the instant you commit and her W true damage races your execute threshold."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After her first item she two-to-three-shots you with W bolts before your single burst can finish, and Condemn's wall-stun blanks the E blink you rely on to close the gap."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Vayne is a duelist nightmare: percent-HP true damage ignores your durability, R stealth dodges your totem placement, and any wall in the lane turns Condemn into a free stun-execute on you."}],"wants":{"you":["Fight in open space so Condemn (E) has no wall to stun you against","Bait Tumble (Q) and Condemn (E) before committing your E gap-close","Buy early armor and health to survive Silver Bolts (W) true damage"],"foe":["Kite with Tumble (Q) to stay outside your Q-nail and W range","Condemn (E) you into a wall the moment you blink in","Pop Final Hour (R) stealth to dodge your Purgatory commit"]},"early":"Vayne out-spaces you from level 1. Tumble keeps her outside your Q-nail range, and Silver Bolts' third-hit true damage cuts through the grey health your W grants, so you take net-negative trades even when you land nails. Never E onto her near a wall or Condemn stuns and executes you. Farm safe, dodge her repositioning, and don't feed her early kills that snowball her scaling.","mid":"Levels 4-6 she only pulls further ahead as her W true damage scales. Level 6 Final Hour is the killer: the Tumble stealth lets her dodge your Purgatory commit and reposition mid-combo, while the AD steroid lets her shred you before your burst lands. Hold E defensively for her all-ins, stay away from walls, and look to roam or trade with jungle help rather than solo her.","late":"Late Vayne is a hard loss for you. Percent-max-HP true damage ignores everything you build, her R stealth beats your totem timing, and Condemn punishes the E blink that is your only gap-close. Buy armor and HP to survive a single rotation, but accept you cannot duel her; play with a frontline that can wall her off and force Condemn before you ever commit.","whys":["Tumble spacing and W true damage beat your level-1 trades.","Silver Bolts shred through your grey health at level 2.","Condemn wall-stun punishes your level-3 E gap-close.","Her kiting and true-damage scaling keep her ahead through 4-5.","Final Hour stealth dodges your Purgatory commit at 6.","Post-item her W bolts out-damage your single burst.","Late, percent-HP true damage and R stealth beat your whole kit."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"vladimir","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Vladimir"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early it's an even skill lane: your Q nails and W burst can chunk his low base durability, but every time you commit he can Sanguine Pool (W) out of your E gap-close and your damage entirely."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Roughly even at 6: your Purgatory (R) can execute him, but his Pool (W) is an untargetable dodge that eats the totem's window, so it becomes a mind-game over baiting the Pool before you commit."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still close after first item, though the tide starts turning; his Transfusion (Q) heal and Crimson Rush let him claw back the HP your burst removes if you can't chain the kill instantly."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Vladimir outscales you hard: Hemoplague (R) amp, massive drain sustain, and Pool to dodge your execute mean he becomes a healing juggernaut your single-target burst can no longer delete."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait Sanguine Pool (W) before committing Purgatory (R) or your E","Rush anti-heal to blunt Transfusion (Q) and his drain sustain","Punish his low levels before his healing and Hemoplague (R) online"],"foe":["Dodge your burst and E with Sanguine Pool (W) untargetability","Out-sustain your poke with Transfusion (Q) between trades","Scale to items where Hemoplague (R) and drains outheal your damage"]},"early":"Early is a genuine skill matchup decided by who respects cooldowns. Your Q-nail poke and W spike can punish Vladimir's flimsy early base stats, but his Sanguine Pool erases any all-in you mistime, so bait it out before you E in. Trade when his Transfusion is on cooldown and his Pool is down. Don't let your W self-damage leave you low into his Q harass while he's healthy.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stay close and hinge on Pool management. At 6 your Purgatory can theoretically execute him, but he'll dodge the window with untargetable Pool, so the fight is a mind-game: force the Pool with a feint, then commit your execute after it's spent. Rush anti-heal to start cutting his drain sustain before his item spikes flip the lane.","late":"Late is where you lose the skill footing: Hemoplague amps his whole team, his drains and item sustain outheal your burst, and Pool keeps dodging your totem. Your single-target execute can't keep up with a fed Vladimir's healing. Prioritize anti-heal and grouping, and rely on hard CC from teammates to catch him out of Pool since you can no longer solo-delete him.","whys":["Even skill lane: your burst and his Pool cancel out at level 1.","Trades stay balanced around Pool and Transfusion cooldowns at 2.","Level 3 remains a skill fight over baiting his escapes.","Neither pulls clearly ahead through levels 4-5.","At 6 his untargetable Pool trades evenly against your execute.","First item stays close but his sustain begins clawing back.","Late, his drains and Hemoplague amp outscale your burst."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"volibear","win":["Volibear","Volibear","Volibear","Volibear","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Volibear owns early levels: his Thundering Smash (Q) run-up stun and Frenzied Maul (W) heal let him bully your Q-nail range, and stepping in to W-burst him just eats his empowered auto and self-heal."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is your window: Purgatory (R) executes him before his sustain runs away, and if you time it as he commits Stormbringer (R), you drop him under the growing threshold instead of letting his ult shields and health save him."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With one AP item your Q-mark plus W grey-health burst finally out-damages a trade, and E's takedown reset lets you dive and delete him when he's chunked below your execute line."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late leans on Skill and totem timing: don't ult him at full HP into his W heal, but a clean burst that sets up Purgatory below threshold still snowballs off his tanky-but-killable profile."}],"wants":{"you":["Hold Purgatory (R) for after he commits Stormbringer (R)","Wait out Frenzied Maul (W) heals before you burst-trade","Dodge Thundering Smash (Q) so he can't stun-start his all-in"],"foe":["Run you down with Thundering Smash (Q) stun into empowered W","Out-sustain your poke with Frenzied Maul (W) between trades","Dive with Stormbringer (R) to bypass your E escape"]},"early":"Volibear pushes you around levels 1-4. His Q run-up gives him a stun to open, and Frenzied Maul heals him through your poke, so committing your W burst just feeds his sustain and empowered autos. Your W self-damage is a liability here. Farm at range, dodge the Q so he can't start his engage, and keep E purely for disengaging his run-downs rather than trading.","mid":"Level 6 flips the lane in your favor. Purgatory is an execute totem, and Volibear's health-and-heal profile is exactly what it's built to punish once you can land it. Don't waste it into a full-HP Frenzied Maul window; bait his Stormbringer dive, survive the initial burst with E, then drop the totem to execute him below the rising threshold. Your first AP item makes the setup burst reliable.","late":"Late is a Skill fight decided by totem discipline. Volibear stays tanky and self-heals, so a mistimed ult into his W does nothing, but a clean combo that chunks him under your execute line still deletes him. Use E's takedown reset to chain kills in fights, and coordinate so he blows Stormbringer before you commit Purgatory for the finish.","whys":["Q stun and W heal let Volibear bully your level-1 range.","His sustain and empowered autos out-trade you at level 2.","Frenzied Maul healing owns the level-3 all-in.","He stays ahead on health and heals through levels 4-5.","At 6 your Purgatory executes his health-and-heal profile.","First-item burst plus a saved execute totem lets you delete him.","Late comes down to Skill and timing the totem past his W heal."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"warwick","win":["Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick","Warwick"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Warwick out-sustains you outright: Jaws of the Beast (Q) heals him for a chunk of the damage dealt, and his passive lifesteal ramps as you drop him low, so your Q-nail poke and W burst just refuel him."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Infinite Duress (R) is a hard-counter to your execute: it's an untargetable leap into a full-duration suppress, so he locks you down and heals through your Purgatory (R) window before you can finish the threshold."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After first item his Q heal plus lifesteal outstat your single burst; you chunk him, he Q's back to health, and his W (Blood Hunt) speed lets him stick to you through your E."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late Warwick is a healing diver you can't delete: his passive heals scale hard when you're low, R suppresses through your E blink, and his sustain simply outlasts your burst-and-execute pattern."}],"wants":{"you":["Rush anti-heal to gut Jaws of the Beast (Q) and his passive lifesteal","Save E to break away from Blood Hunt (W) chases","Never blow Purgatory (R) while his Infinite Duress (R) is available"],"foe":["Heal through your poke with Jaws of the Beast (Q) and passive lifesteal","Track your low HP via Blood Hunt (W) to run you down","Suppress you with Infinite Duress (R) and outheal your execute"]},"early":"Warwick wins from level 1. His Q heals for a portion of the damage it deals and his passive lifesteal grows as his target drops low, so the burst pattern your kit relies on actively feeds him. Your W self-damage makes you the low-HP target his passive loves. Farm at max range, poke only when you can walk away clean, and rush anti-heal to start cutting his sustain.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stay in his favor and 6 is the trap. Infinite Duress is an untargetable leap into a full suppress, which directly answers your execute identity: he locks you, tanks your combo, and heals through your Purgatory before the threshold catches him. Never commit your ult while his R is up. Hold E for the Blood Hunt chase and play for jungle pressure over solo trades.","late":"Late Warwick is a sustain diver who beats your whole gameplan. His passive heals scale with your low HP, his R suppresses through your E blink, and his lifesteal outlasts your single-target burst. Anti-heal is mandatory but not sufficient alone; rely on teammates to peel his Duress and burn his sustain, and only look to execute after his R and heals are spent.","whys":["Warwick's Q heal and lifesteal out-sustain your level-1 poke.","His passive healing off your low HP beats trades at level 2.","Jaws of the Beast sustain owns the level-3 all-in.","His lifesteal keeps him ahead through levels 4-5.","Infinite Duress suppress hard-counters your execute at 6.","Post-item his Q heal and lifesteal outstat your single burst.","Late, his scaling heals and R suppress outlast your whole kit."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"wukong","win":["Wukong","Wukong","Wukong","Wukong","Wukong","Wukong","Wukong"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Wukong's Q auto-reset plus Warrior Trickster clone gives him a bloated all-in every time his Q is up; your W self-damage stacks with his burst, so trading into his clone window gets you killed even when you land Ritual Nails."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Cyclone knocks you up and shreds armor for its full duration; your R Purgatory totem does nothing while you're airborne, and he can spin you out of your own execute zone."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Wukong's first-item armor and Trickster clone let him bait your E dash-through and W commit, then reappear and chunk you; his sustain damage outscales your grey-health steroid."},{"when":"Late","text":"His Cyclone is a teamfight reset button that peels or dives you before your totem threshold matters; you never get a clean solo execute window."}],"wants":{"you":["Freeze short and farm with Q Ritual Nails from max range","Hold E Ashen Pursuit for his clone dropping, not to engage","Buy early armor and Merc treads if he goes crit"],"foe":["Bait your W self-damage then Q-reset onto you","Use clone to dodge your E and R commitment","Land Cyclone to negate your totem entirely"]},"early":"Wukong wins level 1-2 outright: his Crushing Blow (Q) armor shred plus the auto-reset out-trades your Ritual Nails poke, and your W Soul Ignition self-damage makes any bad trade lethal. Last-hit at range and don't walk into his empowered Q.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay red. His Warrior Trickster clone eats your E dash-through and W commit, and at 6 Cyclone knocks you airborne where your R totem does nothing. Never all-in when his Q is up.","late":"With items Wukong's clone-bait and Cyclone reset keep him ahead; his armor and sustain damage beat your grey-health window and he can spin you out of any execute totem you drop.","whys":["Wukong's level-1 Crushing Blow shred and Q reset out-trade your Ritual Nails.","At 2 his armor-shred trade plus your W self-damage make every exchange favour him.","Level 3 Trickster clone lets him bait your E and W and reappear to punish.","Levels 4-5 his Q-reset all-in with clone outdamages your grey-health steroid.","Level 6 Cyclone knocks you airborne and nullifies your R Purgatory totem.","First-item armor and clone-baiting keep Wukong winning the all-in.","Cyclone as a reset and his sustain keep him ahead into every teamfight."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"yasuo","win":["Yasuo","Yasuo","Yasuo","Yasuo","Yasuo","Yasuo","Yasuo"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Yasuo's Wind Wall (W) eats your Q Ritual Nails and any ranged poke, and his double-Q into E dash spacing lets him trade for free; your W self-damage means his knockup burst finishes you fast."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"With flow shield and Q-tornado into R, he all-ins the moment you W-commit; your R Purgatory totem is useless while he airborne-juggles you and the flow shield eats your execute damage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Yasuo's first crit item spikes his auto damage hard; his E-Q mobility dodges your E dash-through and he can flow-shield through your W burst window."},{"when":"Late","text":"He can R off any minion knockup and his sustained crit plus Wind Wall shut down your poke and any totem execute; you rarely get a clean solo kill."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke with Q only when his Wind Wall is down","Save E Ashen Pursuit to escape his E-Q gapclose, not to engage","Rush early armor and stay behind minions to deny his E resets"],"foe":["Block your Q Ritual Nails and poke with Wind Wall","Stack flow shield then all-in your W commit","Knockup-juggle you so your R totem never lands"]},"early":"Yasuo wins the early lane: Wind Wall (W) negates your Q Ritual Nails poke and his passive shield eats chip, while your W self-damage punishes any misstep. Farm safely and don't feed his E dash resets off the minion wave.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay red. His double-Q tornado into E spacing out-trades you, and at 6 he R's off a knockup and juggles you where your Purgatory totem can't execute. Only commit W when Wind Wall and his tornado are both down.","late":"With crit items Yasuo's auto damage and flow shield beat your grey-health steroid, and Wind Wall plus his mobility deny both your poke and any solo execute totem.","whys":["Yasuo's Wind Wall and passive shield blank your level-1 Q poke.","At 2 his shield and E spacing out-trade your Ritual Nails.","Level 3 double-Q into E dash lets him trade for free through your W self-damage.","Levels 4-5 flow shield and mobility beat your grey-health commit.","Level 6 R off a knockup juggles you and nullifies your R totem.","First crit item spikes his autos past your W burst window.","Sustained crit plus Wind Wall shut down your poke and execute late."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"yone","win":["Yone","Yone","Yone","Yone","Yone","Yone","Yone"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Yone's Q third-hit knockup and E soul-dash let him engage and disengage on his terms; your W Soul Ignition self-damage stacks with his mixed burst so a single knockup combo can kill you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Fate Sealed (R) is a point-blank knockup that catches your W commit and E dash; your R Purgatory totem does nothing while you're airborne and he can R you out of the zone."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Yone's first item spikes both his AD and AP scaling; his E return-dash bails him out of your all-in and lets him re-engage when your cooldowns are down."},{"when":"Late","text":"His Q-dash mobility and R engage let him pick when to fight; his mixed damage and E safety mean you never land a clean solo execute totem."}],"wants":{"you":["Trade with Q Ritual Nails only when his Q stacks are reset","Hold E Ashen Pursuit for his E return, not to engage","Build early armor-MR and respect his level-3 knockup"],"foe":["Land Q third-hit knockup into full combo through your W","Use E soul-dash to bail and re-engage safely","Fate Sealed you out of your R totem zone"]},"early":"Yone wins level 1-2: his Q pressure and safety out-trade your Ritual Nails, and your W self-damage makes any bad exchange fatal against his mixed burst. Farm at range and don't get hit by the third-hit Q.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay red. His Q knockup into E soul-dash lets him all-in and escape, and at 6 Fate Sealed catches your W commit and juggles you out of your R totem. Only trade when his E is on cooldown.","late":"With items Yone's mixed AD-AP damage beats your grey-health window; his E return-dash and R engage let him pick fights and dodge any solo execute you set up.","whys":["Yone's level-1 Q pressure and safety out-trade your Ritual Nails.","At 2 his mixed burst plus your W self-damage favour him in trades.","Level 3 Q knockup into E soul-dash lets him all-in and escape.","Levels 4-5 his E safety and burst beat your grey-health commit.","Level 6 Fate Sealed catches your W and nullifies your R totem.","First-item mixed scaling spikes past your W burst window.","E return-dash and R engage let him dictate fights and dodge your execute."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"yorick","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Yorick's ghouls (W cage plus E-marked ghoul swarm) zone you off the wave; your P Silver Stake on-hit and Q Ritual Nails let you burst him if you can dodge the E slow, but respect the Maiden by mid-levels."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is your window: your R Purgatory totem executes Yorick under its threshold before his Maiden can peel, and his lack of mobility means once you E in with W Soul Ignition active he can't escape the totem zone."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Yorick's Maiden and ghoul wall carry his damage and split pressure; his W cage traps your E dash-through and the ghoul swarm out-sustains your grey-health poke if you fight into them."},{"when":"Late","text":"Yorick out-splits and his Maiden plus ghouls beat you in a prolonged fight; roam and use your R execute in skirmishes rather than dueling him under his ghoul army."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge his E slow so his ghouls and Maiden can't stick","All-in at 6 with R Purgatory when he's below the execute threshold","Kill or ignore the Maiden before committing your W"],"foe":["Wall you in with W cage to trap your E dash","Zone you off farm with ghouls and E slow","Out-split and out-sustain with Maiden past laning"]},"early":"Skill matchup early: Yorick's ghouls and E slow zone you, but your P Silver Stake on-hit and Q poke punish him if you avoid the cage and don't feed ghoul stacks. Trade in short windows and back off the Maiden.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay even on skill, then level 6 flips to you: your R Purgatory totem executes an immobile Yorick under its threshold before his Maiden can save him, so E in with W active and finish inside the zone. That ult window is your best kill setup.","late":"After items Yorick's Maiden, ghoul wall and split pressure edge back ahead in a straight duel, so use your R execute in skirmishes and roams rather than fighting into his full ghoul army.","whys":["Even on skill at 1: your P on-hit trades against his ghoul zoning.","Level 2 stays a skill trade around his E slow and ghoul stacks.","Level 3 is even as his cage and ghouls meet your Q poke and burst.","Levels 4-5 remain skill-dependent around Maiden timing and your dodges.","Level 6 favours you: your R totem executes the immobile Yorick before Maiden peels.","First item swings back to skill as his Maiden and ghoul wall come online.","Late stays even-to-skill as his split pressure balances your execute picks."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"zac","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Zac","Skill","Zac","Zac"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zac's blob passive plus Q double-grab and E stretch give him sustain and pick threat; his level-4 spike lets his Elastic Slingshot engage out-range your E, and his healing blobs undo your Q poke and W chip."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even-ish window: your R Purgatory totem can execute Zac under its threshold if he commits, but his passive revive from blobs means you must clear the goo before the totem finishes or he rezzes out of it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Zac's first health item plus blob sustain massively out-heals your grey-health W steroid; his E engage and Q peel let him disrupt your W commit and E dash before you get a clean execute."},{"when":"Late","text":"Zac's huge HP pool, blob revive and AoE CC make him a nightmare for a squishy assassin; his sustain beats your poke and his passive can survive your totem threshold outright."}],"wants":{"you":["Poke with Q and P on-hit but expect his blobs to heal it back","Use R Purgatory only after clearing his passive blobs","Save E Ashen Pursuit to dodge his E Slingshot engage"],"foe":["Sustain through your Q and W chip with blob pickups","Slingshot-engage past your E and Q-grab you","Revive via passive to survive your R execute threshold"]},"early":"Skill matchup at 1-3: your P Silver Stake on-hit and Q poke can chunk Zac, but his blob passive heals most of it back, so trade only when his blobs are gone. Don't get grabbed by his double-Q.","mid":"Level 4-5 tilts to Zac as his Slingshot engage and sustain come online, then 6 is roughly even because your R totem can execute him if he over-commits, provided you clear his blobs so he can't rez out. Respect his E pick threat.","late":"With items Zac's health stacking, blob revive and AoE CC beat your grey-health window and can outright survive your execute threshold; play for skirmish picks rather than dueling his HP pool.","whys":["Even on skill at 1 as your on-hit poke meets his blob sustain.","Level 2 stays a skill trade around his healing blobs.","Level 3 remains even as your Q burst trades with his sustain.","Levels 4-5 favour Zac: Slingshot engage and blob sustain spike him.","Level 6 is even-ish as your R totem can execute an over-committed Zac.","First health item and blob revive out-heal your grey-health steroid.","Late Zac's HP pool and revive survive your poke and execute threshold."]},
  {"a":"locke","b":"ziggs","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ziggs pokes with Bouncing Bomb (Q) and zones with W Satchel and E minefield; you have to walk the wave sidestepping Q, but his short range on everything means your Q Ritual Nails slow and P on-hit set up your gap-close."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is your kill window: E Ashen Pursuit blinks over his E minefield, W Soul Ignition burst plus R Purgatory execute delete an immobile Ziggs, and his only escape is W Satchel self-knockback which you can pre-empt."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Ziggs' first AP item spikes his Q poke and waveclear hard; if you can't reach him he pushes you in and chunks you, and his E minefield plus W knockback deny your E engage angle."},{"when":"Late","text":"With items Ziggs out-ranges and out-pokes you in any open fight and his R gives global pressure; you must use your E and R to burst him in a sidelane pick before he can Satchel away."}],"wants":{"you":["Sidestep Q Bouncing Bomb and walk up behind minions","All-in at 6: E over the minefield, W plus R to execute","Dodge his E minefield line before committing your dash"],"foe":["Poke you down with Q and zone with E minefield","W Satchel knockback to escape your E gap-close","Out-range and push you in after his first AP item"]},"early":"Skill matchup early: Ziggs' Q poke and E minefield zone you, but everything he has is short-cast, so sidestep the bomb, use Q Ritual Nails slow and P Silver Stake on-hit, and walk up behind the wave. Don't eat free Q bounces.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay even on skill, then level 6 flips to you: E Ashen Pursuit blinks over his minefield and W Soul Ignition plus R Purgatory execute an immobile Ziggs before his W Satchel can knock him clear. That all-in is your best kill.","late":"After his first AP item Ziggs out-ranges and out-pokes you in open fights, so force sidelane picks with your E and R execute rather than trading into his poke from the front.","whys":["Even on skill at 1 as his Q poke meets your Q slow and on-hit setup.","Level 2 stays a skill trade around his Q range and your walk-up.","Level 3 remains even as his E minefield trades with your gap-close threat.","Levels 4-5 stay skill-dependent around dodging Q and his zoning.","Level 6 favours you: E over the minefield plus W and R execute the immobile Ziggs.","First AP item swings poke back to Ziggs as he out-ranges you.","Late stays even-to-skill as his poke balances your sidelane execute picks."]}
